TEXT.Text:
{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak to Great Wizard Edeline

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Edeline

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Edeline{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has finished her analysis of the egg that Kyero delivered. She has concluded that it is still in the early stages of development. She is suggesting we make an incubator to ensure the egg hatches successfully. Talk to {C=0xFF00863C/}Edeline{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to find out what is required.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Create a Portable Magic Book

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Julie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Julie suggested you create a Portable Magic Book using the Extract Magical Force Ingredient.
Use your {C=0xFFFF5917/}Extract Magical Force Ingredient{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to create a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Portable Magic Book{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Once you have created it take it to {C=0xFF00863C/}Julie{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

(Right click on the Extract Magical Force Ingredient in your Inventory to open the window which will allow you to create the Portable Magic Book. You need to have learnt 'Extract Magical Force' first.)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver the Chocolate Cake to Sofia at Port of the Winds.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Sofia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rony received a valentines chocolate cake from Sofia, but the chocolate cake is far too bitter to eat! Rony doesn't want to tell Sofia her cake tastes bad and hurt her feelings.
Deliver the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Chocolate Cake{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to {C=0xFFFF5917/}Sofia{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and let her taste the cake.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak with Gordon at Port of the Winds.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds (Valentines) - Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sofia made a chocolate cake using chocolate made by the Master Chocolatier. We need to find why the Master Chocolatier's chocolate does not taste heavenly anymore.
Report this to Detective Gordon for Sofia.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Battle Pet Advancement Kit

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Amy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You need a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Battle Pet Advancement Kit{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to proceed with the 1st class promotion for your riding pet. You can easily get a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Battle Pet Advancement Kit{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFF00863C/}Pet Merchant Amy's{C=0xFF4D0D08/} shop.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Enter the Cookie Factory's Master Chocolatier's House(F6) and investigate the Love Haters.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds (Valentines) - Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
If you go into the entrance on the right, you can enter the Master Chocolatier's House(F6). Inside the Love Haters members are acting suspiciously. Please investigate {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Bakery Guards{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Candy Shop Guards{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Icecream Store Guards{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and find out what they're up to.
Speak to Yamaki to enter the Cookie Factory, he stands next to Gordon.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Enter the Master Chocolatier's House (F6) in the Cookie Factory and defeat 10 Well Done Cookies, 10 Undercooked Cookies and 10 Chocolate Cookies.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds (Valentines) - Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gordon has discovered that the taste of the chocolate has become very bitter because the Love Haters have been interfering with the Gingerbread Man's work. Gordon wants you to defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Well Done Cookies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Undercooked Cookies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Chocolate Cookies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}Master Chocolatier's House(F6){C=0xFF4D0D08/} inside the Cookie Factory.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Stop Ademia and the Love Haters at the Cookie Factory Master Chocolatiers House (F6)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds (Valentines) - Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gordon discovered that the Love Haters are being led by Ademia who wants to interfere with the Gingerbread Mans work. If there is going to be any sweet chocolate this Valentines we need to stop Ademia from interfering, you can find her at Stage 10 of the Cookie Factory Master Chocolatiers House (F6).

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak with Walter at Port of the Winds.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Walter

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gordon says Ademia is causing the trouble at the Master Chocolatiers House because she is lonely. Ademia needs a Valentine to, Walter claims he has many friends, one of them might be a perfect match. Speak with him and find out if anyone comes to mind.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Amy at the Port of the Winds.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Amy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Walter does not have many close friends, but since you went to speak to him he's asked you for help. Walter would like you to check if the Valentines Chocolates he sent to Amy have arrived safely.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Maytry

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Maytry

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Drakan Priest Maytry found you where you crash landed in {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Talk to Maytry, he will help you recover.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 5 Crabbies at Bearded Whale Coast 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Maytry

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Maytry want's to know how your recovery is going. She wants to promote you to a {C=0xFF016295/}Superior Summoner{C=0xFF4D0D08/} after you have fully recovered. Kill 5 {C=0xFFFF0000/}Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to test whether you have fully recovered or not.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 5 Crabbies at Bearded Whale Coast 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Maytry

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Maytry wants to know how your recovery is going. She wants to promote you to a {C=0xFF016295/}Amazonian{C=0xFF4D0D08/} after you have fully recovered. Kill 5 {C=0xFFFF0000/}Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to test whether you have fully recovered or not.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 25 Skelldrark and Darkness Watchman at Edge of the world

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Jundo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The veteran {C=0xFF00863C/}Garrison base Commander Jundo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} will not allow a weak warrior to enter Black Claw Nest Outpost.
Prove to him you are strong enough to enter, kill 25 {C=0xFFFF0000/}Skelldrark and Darkness Watchman{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Edge of the world{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain a Piece of the Dark abyss from Kashape at Edge of the World

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Jundo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFFFF5917/}Kashape{C=0xFF4D0D08/} who is now at Edge of the World is the one who attracted a lot of the spirit monsters from the Dark Abyss. {C=0xFF00863C/}Garrison base Commander Jundo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has promised to permit the person who kills {C=0xFFFF5917/}Kashape{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Edge of the world[Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and returns with a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Piece of Dark Abyss{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to join the Dragon Expedition.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak with Gordon at Port of the Winds

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds (Valentines) - Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Amy says the chocolate ordered by Walter hasn't arrived yet. There is rumour going around saying that chocolates are disappearing from the Cookie Factory, and Gordon is looking into the situation. Speak to Gordon at Port of the Winds to find out what's going on.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Enter the Cookie Factory Chocolate Storehouse (F7) and investigate 50 ChocoChop.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds (Valentines) - Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Retrieve 20 Chocolate boxes from the Pudding Monsters in the Cookie Factory Chocolate Storehouse(F7)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds (Valentines) - Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gordon is struggling to handle all of the complaints from everyone who's Chocolate Boxes have gone missing! Walter is making an especially big fuss about it, they are desperate to get the chocolate in time for Valentines!
Gordon would like you to retrieve {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Chocolate Boxes{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Pudding Monsters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Cookie Factory Chocolate Storehouse (F7){C=0xFF4D0D08/} immediately, before the crowd overcomes him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Stop Coofie, boss of the Chocolate Robbers at the Cookie Factory Chocolate Storehouse (F7).

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds (Valentines) - Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gordon discovered that the boss behind the Chocolate Robbers is called Coofie. Clear the {C=0xFF016295/}Chocolate Storehouse (F7){C=0xFF4D0D08/} Stage 40 and find out why {C=0xFFFF5917/}Coofie{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is stealing the chocolate.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Introduce Ademia to Coofie at the Cookie Factory Chocolate Storehouse(F7).

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds  (Valentines) - Gordon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gordon thinks this whole incident at the Cookie Factory has happened because of Coofie's and Ademia's loneliness. He thinks if we can get them to meet their loneliness can be ended and it will stop them from cause anymore trouble. Stop {C=0xFFFF5917/}Coofie{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from doing anything more stupid before meeting Ademia by clearing the Cookie Factory {C=0xFF016295/}Chocolate Storehouse (F7) Stage 40{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Dun Morgan in Odelia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Dun Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mukapa warns that adventurers can encounter many surprises when they are travelling, he suggests it would be wise to learn some Instant Processing skills to support you when the going gets tough. Instant Cooking can be learned from {C=0xFF00863C/}Brutus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in Port of the Winds, Blacksmith {C=0xFF00863C/}Davi{C=0xFF4D0D08/} teaches you Simple Crafting and  Soul Craft Merchant {C=0xFF00863C/}Julie{C=0xFF4D0D08/} shares extracting magical force.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gain 10 Firewood from Shark Pirates at the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Brutus

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Brutus believes that a chef needs to cook with passion. To prove you have a passion for cooking, bring him some Firewood. You can get some Firewood from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Bring 10 pieces of {C=0xFFFF5917/}Firewood{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to Brutus.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Make a Portable Snack using the Instant Cooking Ingredient

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Brutus

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF016295/}Brutus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} gave you a Instant Cooking Ingredient and suggested you try to cook with it! Double-click the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Instant Cooking Ingredient{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and use the pop-up window to create a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Portable Snack{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Take the Snack to {C=0xFF016295/}Brutus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to see what he thinks!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 10 Fleece from Shark Deckhands at the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Davi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Davi says that you can create powerful equipment through Simple Crafting using the loot you collect from Monsters. It's not an easy skill to teach so Davi is only willing to teach Skillful Craftsmen like him. He is willing to teach you in exchange for
10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Fleece{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Create a Portable Armor Kit using the Simple Crafting Ingredient

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Davi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Davi has given you a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Simple Crafting Ingredient{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to create a Armour Kit with. Double click the Simple Crafting Ingredient and in the pop-up window create a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Portable Armour Kit{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
When you're finished take it to {C=0xFFFF5917/}Davi{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Soul Craft Merchant Julie in Port of the Winds

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Julie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Items you can Extract Magical Force from can be obtained by hunting all kinds of monsters.
You can Extract Magical Force and use it for something else you wish to make, but Julie says there is no such thing as a free lunch. She is only willing to share her secrets on how to Extract Magical Force in exchange for {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Souls{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Take them to Julie to learn the secrets.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Using Extract Magical Force Ingredient, Make Portable Magic book

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Julie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFFFF5917/}Julie{C=0xFF4D0D08/} suggested to Make Portable Magic book using {C=0xFFFF5917/}Ingredient for extracting magical force{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Double-click {C=0xFFFF5917/}Ingredient for extracting magical force{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to Open pop-up window to Make {C=0xFFFF5917/}Portable Magic book{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Using Extract Magical Force Ingredient, Make {C=0xFFFF5917/}Portable Magic book{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and bring it to {C=0xFFFF5917/}Julie{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Tailring in Port of the Winds.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Tailring

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Kafra Employee Tailring is seeking a hero who can save the world of {C=0xFF016295/}Ragnarök{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFF016295/}Geffen{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Since the dimensional resistance is placed over the world of {C=0xFF016295/}Ragnarök{C=0xFF4D0D08/} the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Ragnarök Novice set{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is needed to avoid it! If the Ragnarök Novice Set is not equipped then your movement speed will only be 50% of your original speed!

Sigh, I can't blame you. After all, you don't look like a true hero.
Too bad, I shall wait here for a real hero i guess.%%
{C=0xFF00863C/}(How can you tell who is a hero?){C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Tailring in Geffen

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Geffen - Tailring

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tailring says there is a dimensional eye that interacts between {C=0xFF016295/}Geffen{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and Port of the Winds as a bridge when passing through a dimension, {C=0xFF00863C/}(Tailring){C=0xFF4D0D08/} asks to visit her.

Hmm? You want to make a testament before you go?
Good decision. Our world is very dangerous.%%
{C=0xFF00863C/}(Advice? Or Insult?){C=0xFF4D0D08/}

Yes, you are right! We don't have to go in a rush.
I haven't done any shopping yet.%%
{C=0xFF00863C/}(You came for shopping?){C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Deporte in Geffen

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Geffen - Deporte

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tailring has not been to {C=0xFF016295/}Geffen{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for a long time and now she is not sure of how {C=0xFF016295/}Geffen{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is these days. She suggests that you go talk to {C=0xFF00863C/}Deporte{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for more details! Visit {C=0xFF016295/}Geffen{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and talk to {C=0xFF00863C/}Deporte{C=0xFF4D0D08/}!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Deporte in Geffen

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Geffen - Deporte

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Deporte{C=0xFF4D0D08/} explains why the Extremists and Moderates have been in conflict. And now the biggest problem they face is not the mutated monsters but the dimensional vortex that is proliferating these days. Ask {C=0xFF00863C/}Deporte{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for more details!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 5 pieces of Proof of mutation from Poring in the Orc Field

