Get training from advanced class mangers in Fungoid Village. 
The first task would be perform a 200-hit combo on the monsters in {C=0xFF016295/}Tutu Tree Forest{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Meet Chief Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungoid Village - Meet Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Being able to perform powerful combat moves is great, but sometimes you need to use your mind to keep the peace.
Go to Cheif Fungarf and teach him how to how to have a heart, like a Drakan.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Receive Spiritual Protection Stones from Gwen

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Gwen

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gwen is warning all adventurers that the {C=0xFF016295/}Guardians' Dungeon{C=0xFF4D0D08/} are fraught with danger. The high concentrations of Spiritual Energy inside can have adverse effects on all those who enter, Gwen is offering Spiritual Protection Stones to all those who do not heed her warnings of the dangers inside.
The stones will provide you protection from the Spiritual Energy inside but the stones drain your own Spiritual Energy, you can use no more than four a day for your own safety.
Talk to Gwen and earn four {C=0xFFFF0000/}Spiritual Protection Stones{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Conversation with Randy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Randy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Randy is tired of the Halloween Ghosts that appear on every Halloween. Randy has prepared some treats for Halloween but the Halloween Ghosts have stolen and hidden all of them in the giant pumpkins. The ghosts then cast some tricks on the pumpkins and now they have become dangerous Tricked Pumpkins!
The Halloween Ghosts are not going to clean up the chaos they have caused, Randy wants to punish them for stealing all the treats from him!
Punish the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Halloween Ghosts{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and enjoy the treats Randy prepared for you. {C=0xFFFF5917/}Tricked Pumpkins{C=0xFF4D0D08/} appear in random places, so you will have to search for them!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Earn 20 Halloween Tokens from Halloween Ghosts

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Randy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Randy heard about ghost hunters. But he has never seen one. Randy believes ghost hunters who capture evil ghosts are marvellous beings. To praise ghost hunters, he has prepared Halloween Tokens. But evil Halloween Ghosts have stolen them. For poor Randy, defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Halloween Ghosts{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take back 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Halloween Tokens{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Halloween Ghosts are hiding inside {C=0xFFFF5917/}Tricked Pumpkins{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. You can find pumpkins in various fields. So keep looking.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring 1 Ghost Soul from a Ghost Hunter to Randy 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Randy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Randy obtained a special item from an old man wearing red clothes in Halloween Town. He told Randy that in order to use the item it first needs to be purified.
Gather a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Ghost Soul{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Randy and receive a special buff in return. Gather more for better buffs, there are four different buffs in total. Let's find {C=0xFFFF0000/}Halloween Ghosts{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from inside the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Tricked Pumpkins{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the fields.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Max to learn a Profession

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Max

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Max has given you the tools required for Production and Processing but that doesn't mean you can just start work right away.
You will have to learn the skills required to handle the tools safely and effectively. Talk to {C=0xFF00863C/}Max{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and ask him how to learn the skills.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Senior Production Master Bessie at the Farm

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Farm - Bessie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Max confessed he did not achieve the title of Production Master easily. The become the best he had to first find the best teacher, luckily while searching he found the Senior Production Master and with her help Max achieved marvelous improvements in his skill.
The Senior Production Master, {C=0xFF00863C/}Bessie{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is currently staying at the {C=0xFF016295/}Farm{C=0xFF4D0D08/} with her two apprentices. She may have time to offer you some help, go and talk to her, remember to tell her Max sent you.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 5 Dried Branches

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Farm - Bessie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
To begin logging, go to the area marked with an axe on the minimap, equip your axe, stand next to one of the signs marked 100, and when it begins flashing you can start logging. Collect {C=0xFFFF5917/}5 Dried Branches{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take them to {C=0xFF00863C/}Bessie{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to collect your reward.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 5 Mineral Fragments

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Farm - Bessie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
To begin mining you need to first learn the {C=0xFF016295/}Mining Skill{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and equip a {C=0xFF016295/}Collecting tool{C=0xFF4D0D08/. Once you have done this, head to the Mining Area and pick a spot with a 100 sign. When the sign begins to flash you can start mining. Mine {C=0xFFFF5917/}5 Mineral Fragments{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take them to {C=0xFF00863C/}Bessie{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 5 Deep Green Leaves

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Farm - Bessie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Herbalism Area is located where the Plough Symbol is shown on the minimap. Go there and find a ploughing place next to a 100 sign. Equip your {C=0xFF016295/}Collecting tool{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and begin ploughing near the place when the light is flashing to collect some leaves. Obtain {C=0xFFFF5917/}5 Deep Green Leaves{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take them to {C=0xFF00863C/}Bessie{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak with Max

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Max

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bartie suggests that since you have had your Job Promotion you should learn a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Production Profession{C=0xFF4D0D08/} so you can gather and produce your own items. Go to the Centre of {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and look for {C=0xFF016295/}Production Master Max{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to learn more about Production Professions.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak with Max

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Max

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bartie suggests that since you have had your Job Promotion you should learn a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Production Profession{C=0xFF4D0D08/} so you can gather and produce your own items. Go to the Centre of {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and look for {C=0xFF016295/}Production Master Max{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to learn more about Production Professions.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Catch 5 Young Fish

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Farm - Bessie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Learn how to fish by firstly finding a good {C=0xFF016295/}Fishing Spot{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for your Fishing Experience Level and then equip your {C=0xFF016295/}Collecting tool{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. When you are at a suitable area you can begin fishing. Start fishing at your chosen spot and catch {C=0xFFFF5917/}5 Young Fish{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take them back to {C=0xFF00863C/}Bessie{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tianshan Snow Lotus from Tool Merchant Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Syari

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You need a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Tianshan Snow Lotus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to proceed with 2nd  promotion for your riding pet. You can easily get a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Tianshan Snow Lotus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFF00863C/}Tool Merchant Hime{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, it's not cheap though!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Dun Morgan in Odelia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Dun Morgan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dun Morgan is advising all adventurers passing through Odelia that each of them should learn the following three skills to make their adventure more fun. Instant Cooking, Simple Crafting and Extract Magical Force.
Instant Cooking can be learnt from {C=0xFF00863C/}Brutus{C=0xFF4D0D08/},
Simple Crafting can be learnt from {C=0xFF016295/}Darwin{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and
Extract Magical Force can be learnt from {C=0xFF016295/}Julie{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. They all live in Odelia.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gather 5 Firewood from Woodies in Windia Plains [Arcade Mode (F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Brutus

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Brutus believes that a chef has to cook with passion, prove to him you have a passion to cook by bringing him {C=0xFFFF5917/}5 Firewood{C=0xFF4D0D08/} obtained from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Woodies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Windia Plains [Arcade Mode (F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to keep his fire burning. Without it he cannot continue cooking for his customers!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Create a Portable Snack

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Brutus

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Brutus is very hungry, he would like you to take his Instant Cooking Ingredient and create him a Portable Snack to eat.
Find the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Instant Cooking Ingredient{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in your inventory and create a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Portable Snack{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take it to {C=0xFF00863C/}Brutus{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

(Right click on the Instant Cooking Ingredient in your Inventory to open the window which will allow you to create the Portable Snack. You need to have learnt 'Instant Cooking' first.)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 5 Fleece from Sheep in Windia Plains[Arcade Mode (F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Darwin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Darwin is saying that using items obtained after defeating monsters you can create great equipments through Simple Crafting. But since this skill is hard to learn, only skillful craftsman like him can do it. But he is willing to teach the skill in exchange of 5 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Fleece{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Sheep{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Windia Plains[Arcade Mode (F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} or {C=0xFF016295/}Advanced Windia Plains{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Windia Plains[Arcade Mode (F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and obtain 5  {C=0xFFFF5917/}Fleece{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Sheep{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Create a Portable Armour Kit

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Darwin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Darwin has given you a Simple Crafting Ingredient and suggests you create a Armour Kit with it. Use the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Simple Crafting Ingredient{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and create a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Portable Armour Kit{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Once you have created it take it to {C=0xFF00863C/}Darwin{C=0xFF4D0D08/} so he can judge it's quality.

(Right click on the Simple Crafting Ingredient in your Inventory to open the window which will allow you to create the Portable Armour Kit. You need to have learnt 'Simple Crafting' first.)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Soul Craft Merchant Julie in Odelia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Julie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Items you can Extract Magical Force from can be obtained by hunting all kinds of monsters.
You can Extract Magical Force and use it for something else you wish to make, but Julie says there is no such thing as a free lunch. She is only willing to share her secrets on how to Extract Magical Force in exchange for {C=0xFFFF5917/}1 Souls{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Take them to Julie to learn the secrets.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Conversation with the Fairy of Winter Nia at the Port of Winds.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Nia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rudolph says he is not good at speaking to the ladies, he has asked you to talk to the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Fairy of Winter{C=0xFF4D0D08/} {C=0xFFFF5917/}Nia{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
Talk to the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Fairy of Winter{C=0xFF4D0D08/} {C=0xFFFF5917/}Nia{C=0xFF4D0D08/} about {C=0xFF00863C/}Santa Claus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the center of Port of the Winds.

{C=0xFF00863C/}(Shocked){C=0xFF4D0D08/}
What? Sa...{C=0xFF00863C/}Santa Claus{C=0xFF4D0D08/}?
Ha..Have I seen him?

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Conversation with the Fairy of Spring Waltz at Port of Winds.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Waltz

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Nia is acting very strange. Speak with the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Fairy of Spring{C=0xFF4D0D08/} {C=0xFFFF5917/}Waltz{C=0xFF4D0D08/} standing next to Nia, about {C=0xFF00863C/}Santa Claus{C=0xFF4D0D08/}!

Now hurry!
I do not know any other details.%%
{C=0xFF00863C/}(Nia is strangely blushing.){C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Look for the Red Sack at the Ice Palace [Arcade Mode (F1)]!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Rudolph

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Waltz think that {C=0xFF00863C/}Santa Claus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} went to the {C=0xFF016295/}Ice Palace{C=0xFF4D0D08/} {C=0xFF016295/}[Arcade Mode (F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Defeat {C=0xFFFF0000/}BearDolly{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at [Arcade Mode (F1)] and bring back the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Red Sack{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to Rudolph in {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/}!
The entrance to the {C=0xFF016295/}Ice Palace{C=0xFF4D0D08/} can be found near the Fairy of Spring, Waltz.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Find the Lost Gift Box at the Ice Palace [Arcade Mode (F1)]!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Rudolph

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
It is believed that at the {C=0xFF016295/}Ice Palace{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Santa Artemis{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Santa Armis{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Lost Present Box{C=0xFF4D0D08/}! Retrieve the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Lost Present Box{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFF016295/}Ice Palace{C=0xFF4D0D08/} {C=0xFF016295/}[Arcade Mode (F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Conversation with the Countess Mary at the Ice Palace [Chaos Map(F2)].

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Waltz

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
She says that from the {C=0xFF016295/}Ice Palace{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFF00863C/}Santa Claus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Countess Mary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} came together. Have a conversation with {C=0xFFFF5917/}Countess Mary{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. {C=0xFFFF5917/}Countess Mary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is at the {C=0xFF016295/}Ice Palace{C=0xFF4D0D08/} {C=0xFF016295/}[Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Conversation with the Queen of Snow Batore at the Ice Palace [Scenario (F5)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Nia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Have a conversation with the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Queen of Snow Batore{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to find out why she summoned {C=0xFF00863C/}Santa Claus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Ice Palace{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
{C=0xFFFF5917/}Queen of Snow Batore{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is at the {C=0xFF016295/}Ice Palace{C=0xFF4D0D08/} {C=0xFF016295/}[Scenario Mode (F5)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rescue Santa Claus from the Ice Palace [Defense Mode (F6)]!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Nia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Save {C=0xFF00863C/}Santa Claus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the Queen of Snow at {C=0xFF00863C/}Ice Palace{C=0xFF4D0D08/} {C=0xFF00863C/}[Defense Mode (F6)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring Santa Present Pouch back to Rudolph in Port of Winds!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Rudolph

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring back {C=0xFFFF5917/}Santa Present Pouch{C=0xFF4D0D08/} that has been given away by Santa to the {C=0xFFFF5917/}monsters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF00863C/}Ice Palace{C=0xFF4D0D08/}!

{C=0xFF00863C/}(Rudolph puts his hand on your shoulder){C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hey! Can't you hear what this reindeer is saying?%%
