Obtain 1 Wooden pickaxe, Candle and Torch

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Valid Raeth - Turner

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Turner is impressed with your skill in battle, he has asked you to get back his equipment from the Skull Clubbers. Get back his {C=0xFFFF5917/}Wooden Pickaxe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Candle{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and{C=0xFFFF5917/}Torch{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the Skull Clubbers at {C=0xFF016295/}Valid Raeth[Mission Mode]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and return them  to {C=0xFF00863C/}Miner Turner{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver the Torch to Jaed

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Valid Raeth - Turner

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Turner wants to tell Jaed that he found  a SOS message on a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Wooden Torch{C=0xFF4D0D08/} which he took from a Skeleton. Deliver the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Wooden Torch{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to {C=0xFF00863C}Guard Jaed{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Valid Raeth{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Miner Turner

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Valid Raeth - Turner

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jaed thinks the missing merchant might have left a SOS message for us, so he has decided he wants to find the Magma Coral Fields' tribe's base camp. Ask {C=0xFF00863C/}Miner Turner{C=0xFF4D0D08/} where you can find the Magma Coral Fields' tribe's base camp.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Enter Elite room at Valid Raeth[Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Valid Raeth - Jaed

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jaed's request to deploy soldiers to provide support for Chief Sambaba's investigation has been rejected. Go to the Elite room at {C=0xFF016295}Valid Raeth[Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} which is the base camp for Magma Coral Fields' tribe to search for {C=0xFF00863C/}Guard Jaed{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. You don't need to fight with Sambaba.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Pablo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Pablo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jaed thinks the Magma Coral Fields' tribe's Stone Board he kept is important evidence regarding the merchant's kidnapping. Deliver the Cuneiform script to {C=0xFF00863C/}Arcanist Pablo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Libra{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Jaed.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Guard Captain Hoffman

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Hoffman

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pablo told you that the Magma Coral Fields' tribe kidnapped the merchants because they feel anxious about the Stone Board. 
Pass this information to {C=0xFF00863C/}Guard Captain Hoffman{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Libra{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Guard Jaed

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Valid Raeth - Jaed

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Guard Captain Hoffman knows how serious the situation is but he said he need to do more investigation to make sure because there is not enough soldiers left in the army to deploy. Speak to {C=0xFF00863C/}Guard Jaed{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Valid Raeth{C=0xFF4D0D08/} about Guard Captain Hoffman's opinion.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Chief Rokko

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Valid Raeth - Jaed

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jaed is planning to give up the search for the missing merchants.
Kill Chief Rokko at {C=0xFF016295/}Valid Raeth[Scenario Mode(F5)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Guard Jaed{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Duke Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Smoldering Swamp - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
A man with a high decree has come to {C=0xFF016295/}Smoldering Swamp{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Guard Captain Hoffman's request has requested you go to
{C=0xFF016295/}Smoldering Swamp{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and find {C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 15 Firefly Needles

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Smoldering Swamps - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is a very fussy collector only interested in collecting special items rather than simple treasures. Kill Fireflies at {C=0xFF016295/}Smoldering Swamps{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and obtain 15 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Firefly Needles{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Dile Bone and obtain 15 Skeleton Tomahawks

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Smoldering Swamp - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is very interested in Dile Bone's weapon. Kill Dile Bone at {C=0xFF016295/}Smoldering Swamp{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and obtain his {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skeleton Tomahawk{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Ribbits and get 10 Batocksin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Smoldering Swamps - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The poison that can be obtained from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Ribbits{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has an effect which causes the consumer to have a smaller face. Kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Ribbits{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Alligator Swamp{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and obtain 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Batocksin{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Count Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and give them to him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 5 Swamp Monster's Hair Decorations

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Smoldering Swamp - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect {C=0xFFFF5917/}5 Swamp monster's hair decorations{C=0xFF4D0D08/}known as the panacea and take them to {C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. He is currently suffering from Batocksin's side-effect and needs the panacea immediately. You can obtain Swamp Monster's hair decorations from Swamp Monsters around {C=0xFF016295/}Petrified Swamp{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 1 Nagaui Javelin, Nagaui Belt, and Nagaui Staff

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Smoldering Swamp - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Monadron is very interested in weapons from the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Webfoot tribe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Kill {C=0xFFFF0000/}Webfoot tribe{C=0xFF4D0D08/} members at {C=0xFF016295/}Reed Swamp{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and obtain 1 of each, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Nagaui Javelin, Nagaui Belt, and Nagaui Staff{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Queen Vella's Royal Jelly

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Smoldering Swamp - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Monadron told you that the Black Witch is the one who revived the Fireflies Queen Vella. Deliver {C=0xFFFF0000/}Queen Vella's Royal Jelly{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to Monadron. You can find Queen Vella at {C=0xFF016295/}Smoldering Swamp[Scenario Mode(F5){C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Guard Captain Hoffman

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Hoffman

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Scientist Noel discovered that Dr. Farrell has been cloning dragons after investigating Dr. Farrell's lab. Give this news to {C=0xFF00863C/}Guard Captain Hoffman{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, you can find him in {C=0xFF016295/}Libra{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Arcanist Pablo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Pablo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Guard Captain Hoffman is worried about you, he heard you wanted to go kill Drake Lavalon alone. Drake Lavalon is very powerful but, he will allow you to go if Pablo approves. Go and find {C=0xFF00863C/}Arcanist Pablo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Libra{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Purify Precious treasure of Fire

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Precious treasure of Fire

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Priest Bartie has worked out that the Precious treasure of Fire is the source of Magma Drake Lavalon's dark power. He has asked you to purify the treasure. Kill Magma Drake Lavalon at {C=0xFF016295/}Magmus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and purify the {C=0xFF00863C/}Precious treasure of Fire{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Priest Horn Ochukoe

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ochukoe

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Priest Bartie tells you about the precious treasure's vicious spirit called Akanai who sentenced Yanai to death. Go back to {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} where the Drakan warriors are returning to and find {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Horn Ochukoe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Guard Captain Hoffman

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Hoffman

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Chief Scientist Noel is expecting you to investigate the precious treasure at the Drakan's hometown in Kazeura Village. He asked you to go and listen to  {C=0xFF00863C/}Guard Captain Hoffman's{C=0xFF4D0D08/} story at {C=0xFF016295/}Libra{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Priest Horn Ochukoe

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ochukoe

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
From Chief Scientist Noel, Guard Captain Hoffman has discovered how dangerous Precious Treasure can be. Hoffman asked you to go to {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and kill Akanai. Proceed to {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and meet {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Horn Ochukoe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver Tianshan Snow Lotus to Syari

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Syari

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Syari examined Feilon and said a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Tianshan Snow Lotus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} before he can become a riding pet. Go and buy a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Tianshan Snow Lotus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the potion shop in {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and deliver it to {C=0xFF00863C/}Archpriest of Earth Syari{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to the former boss, Ranotah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ranotah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Priest Horn Ochukoe feels sad that {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, a place of such paradise, is experiencing such a crisis. Ranotah is already assigned to guide the village's warriors, go and find {C=0xFF00863C/}Ranotah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 40 Potchi at Eruda Valley

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ranotah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Royal Guard Ranotah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} informed us that since the Precious Treasure got polluted, the Potchis have been abusive and attack the people passing by {C=0xFF016295/}Eruda Valley{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Eruda Valley{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat 40 Potchis.(it can be any Potchis.)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Obculling at Eruda Valley

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ranotah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Royal Guard Ranotah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} informed that other animals that eat the plants Potchi grow is turning abusive these days. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Eruda Valley{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Obculling and Red Obculling{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for total 30 of them.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 20 Thorny Potchi and Lotus Potchi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ranotah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}My former boss, Ranotah, {C=0xFF4D0D08/}is saying that the reason why the animals nearby Kazeura became violent is because they have been poisoned by a potent potion. Kill 20 poisoned {C=0xFFFF0000/}Spiny Potchi and Lotus Potchi{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Eruda Valley{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect Poison tester Charm from Salvalon's Cumba

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ranotah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
According to {C=0xFF00863C/}Royal Guard Ranotah{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, Archpriest of Wind Quywcha attached a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Poison tester Charm{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to Cumba's body to investigate the poison which has infected the Cumbas. Kill Cumbas at {C=0xFF016295/}Salvalon{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and obtain a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Poison tester Charm{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 40 Rami and Potchi in Salvalon

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ranotah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Royal Guard Ranotah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} informed that other animals that eat the plants {C=0xFFFF5917/}Potchi{C=0xFF4D0D08/} grow is becoming abusive due to being poisoned with the Black Witch's poison.
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Salvalon{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat 40 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Rami{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Potchi{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for total 40 of them.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Zaro in Salvalon [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Archpriest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/} made a remedy to cure the poisoned animals around Kazeura. To allow the temple people to use the remedy easily, defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Zaro{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFF016295/}Salvalon[Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Zaro in Salvalon [Scenario Mode(F5)].

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ranotah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Royal Guard Ranotah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is blaming himself for teaching martial arts to Cumba.  Enter {C=0xFF016295/}Salvalon [Scenario Mode(F5)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Zaro the King of Cumbas{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver Broken Magic Flute to Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Drakan priest who looks like Yanai is angry with you, {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, as you ruined her plan to persuade Jaro to create a remedy and broke his favourite magic flute. Deliver the {C=0xFFFF0000/}Broken Magic Flute{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get 10 Thick Ebony Wooden Sticks

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Quywcha promised Rue that he would make a new flute using ebony wood for him. Help {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/} by killing Black Kumba in {C=0xFF016295/}Eruda Valley{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Thick Ebony Wooden Stick{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 20 Lami and Horn Lami

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Lamis have been poisoned as they ate Potchi's fruit which was poisoned by the Black Witch. {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is asking you to kill Lamis in {C=0xFF016295/}Salvalon{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Salvalon{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and kill 20 {C=0xFFFF0000/}Lami and Horn Lamis{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 15 Pring Feathers at Lamieta

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Quywcha wants to use the perfect {C=0xFFFF5917/}Pring's Feather{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to make a remedy. Kill Leaf Prings and Black Prings at Lamieta for Quywcha and obtain 15 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Pring's Feathers{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk with Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has realised that disaster is slowly approaching Kazeura because of the tainting of the precious treasure by the Black witch.
Speak with {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and find out what you can do to help.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Black Ebony Stick

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Quywcha told you a story about Kelo and how he became strong by learning ancestral magic from his teacher Brai.  Kill Kelo for priest Quywcha who is willing to make a black ebony flute for you if you can help him. {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mountain Goat Kelo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is in Lamieta [Mission Mode (F5)].

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain the Eight Trigrams of Seven stars from Kelos at Lamieta[Scenario Mode(F5)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village -Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Temple Archpriest Brai discovered the Precious treasure long ago and created the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Eight Trigrams of Seven stars{C=0xFF4D0D08/} which can detect each Precious treasures location, he is afraid it may be abused. According to the temple's warriors, the last person who used the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Eight Trigrams of Seven stars{C=0xFF4D0D08/} was {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/} but, {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/} said she didn't use the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Eight Trigrams of Seven stars{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/} thinks Kelo at Lamieta used some ancestral magic to make himself look like Quywcha and then stole the Eight Trigrams of Seven stars. Quywcha plans to get back the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Eight Trigrams of Seven stars{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from Kelo. 

Kill Kelo at Lamieta [Scenario Mode (F5)] and obtain the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Eight Trigrams of Seven stars{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Danku

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Danku

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
An old man called {C=0xFF00863C/}Danku{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, who you encountered at {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} seemed crazy and gave you a suspicious warning. But the story about the legendary Drakan goddess has given you a strange feeling. 
Listen to {C=0xFF00863C/}Danku{C=0xFF4D0D08/}'s story.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk with Ochukoe

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ochukoe

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/}  has become famous in Kazeura after discovering the Eight Trigrams of Seven stars. Priest Quywcha told {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/} that Priest Horn, Ochukoe is impressed with the great work and that he is looking for him. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and look for {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Horn, Ochukoe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Archpriest of Earth Syari

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Syari

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Priest Horn Ochukoe wants to appoint only the most talent as temple warrior's especially given the current situation. {C=0xFF00863C/}Archpriest of Earth Syari{C=0xFF4D0D08/} will give you the first test. Go and find {C=0xFF00863C/}Archpriest of Earth Syari{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Zaro in Salvalon [Scenario mode(F5)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Syari

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Syari is complaining about some Cumba groups who are attacking the Potchi which are planting the detox seeds. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Salvalon[Scenario mode(F5)]{C=0xFF00863C/} for {C=0xFF4D0D08/}Priest, Syari{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Cumba leader, Zaro{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Archpriest of Wind Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Syari informed you that Archpriest of Wind Quywcha
 will be conducting your second Earth's Test.
Find {C=0xFF00863C/}Archpriest of Wind Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Kelo at Lamieta[Scenario Mode(F5)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Quywcha wants to skip the second test because she is already confident in your abilities, but she has to be fair to the others.
Go to Lamieta[Scenario Mode(F5)] and kill, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Kelo{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Rue at Akia Cave

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Akia Cave - Rue

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Archpriest of Shadow Rue{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is the twin sister of Archpriest of Light Yanai. Quywcha is worried about Rue who has lost her only sister, and has asked you to go and find her. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and find {C=0xFF00863C/}Shadow Archpriest Rue{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Rue at Akia Cave (Near Perry Aerial)

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Akia Cave(Nearby Perry Aerial) - Rue

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Archpriest of Shadow Rue heard from priest Quecah about the tests {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has been taking to become a temple warrior while he was waiting for a shadow flute, so she asked you to complete one of her shadow tests.  Find {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Rue{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Next Floor of Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and speak with her.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Perry Aerial at Akia Cave

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Akia Cave (Near the Spirit of Grudge) - Rue

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rue starts the Shadow's test at {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. To pass the test you need to kill{C=0xFFFF5917/}Perry Aerial{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, the strongest protector of the precious treasure, created by legendary Drakan Brai. Kill Aerial at {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and then find, {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Rue{C=0xFF4D0D08/} near the Spirit of Grudge.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill the Spirit of Grudge at Akia Cave

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Akia Cave(Nearby Bat Spider) - Rue

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rue starts the Fire's test instead of the Temple's Archpriest because he is away, but Rue can't approve you, {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. To pass the Fire's test, kill the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spirit of Grudge{C=0xFF4D0D08/} inside {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and  find {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Rue{C=0xFF4D0D08/} afterwards near the Bat Spider area in {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Bat Spiders at Akia Cave

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Akia Cave (Near Akanai) - Rue

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Rue{C=0xFF4D0D08/} wants you, {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, to pass the Water's test. Go and kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Bat Spiders{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, you must travel {C=0xFF016295/}Deep within Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to find them.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to priest Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Quywcha

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rue says you, {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, have passed the holy test required to become a warrior for the precious treasure place. Go back to {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and speak to {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Quywcha{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Priest Horn Ochukoe

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ochukoe

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
While you were at Akia Cave completing a test, some of the Drakan warriors who had returned from Akia Cave experienced mental blackouts at the village. Go and find {C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Horn Ochukoe{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to become accepted as a warrior for the precious treasure place.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Danku

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Danku

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Danku is a mysterious old Drakan, he thinks it's wrong to purify the precious treasure. He believes in the Drakan's goddess called Origin. Go to find {C=0xFF00863C/}Danku{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, the mysterious old man, and listen to his story.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Akanai

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Ochukoe

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Priest Horn Ochukoe{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is giving orders to all warriors who have come to Kazeura to kill Akanai. Kill the hidden {C=0xFFFF5917/}Tainted precious treasure spirit Akanai{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Perry Aerial

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Akia Cave (Nearby Perry Aerial) - Yanai

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
It seemed like Yanai was dead, but she appeared to me at {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. This must be related to the pollution of the precious treasure. Yanai asked {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to follow her just like she had asked you to follow her before when she was going to kill Akanai. Go to find priest Yanai near {C=0xFF016295/}{C=0xFFFF0000/}Perry Aerial{C=0xFF4D0D08/}{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. You need to kill {C=0xFFFF0000/}Perry Aerial{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to be able to meet Yanai.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Spirit of Grudge 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Akia Cave (Near the Bat Spiders) - Yanai

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
It looks like Yanai, who disappeared very suddenly, is heading deeper into the Cave to find Akanai. Upon Yanai's request, find Yanai who is near the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spirit of Grudge{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. You need to kill the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spirit of Grudge{C=0xFF4D0D08/} before you can meet back up with the {C=0xFF00863C/}Archpriest of Light, Yanai{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Bat Spiders

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Akia Cave (Near Akanai) - Yanai

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Yanai has come to {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/}to find Akanai. She said Akanai who has been released from the Precious Treasure of Earth is looking for the Precious Treasure of Shadow. Upon Yanai's request, try to find Yanai who is near the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Bat Spiders{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. To meet {C=0xFF00863C/}Archpriest of Light, Yanai{C=0xFF4D0D08/} you will need to kill the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Bat Spiders{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Yanai

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Akia Cave (near Akanai) - Yanai

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rue is trying to stop you, {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, from trying to bravely kill the vicious Drakan Ghost, Akanai. You have discovered Rue's real identity, you have many hidden powers {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Rue confessed to you that he is not Yanai. Listen Rue's story about why he need to act like Yanai.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 10 Flying Squirrel and Woods Flying Squirrel 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll - Shangdor

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Shangdor{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is young warrior who is proud to be from the Mika tribe. He wants you to prove your ability if you want to know more about Hell Kaizen. Kill 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Flying Squirrels and Woods Flying Squirrels{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Pinecone Knoll{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Shaman Naoi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll  - Naoi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Shangdor introduced you to the Mika Tribe's Shaman, Naoi. She predicts a future through dreams she has called premonitions. Speak with {C=0xFF00863C/}Mika tribe shaman Naoi{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Pinecone Knoll{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Naoi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll - Naoi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Half a year ago, Naoi dreamed that the world had ended. Because of this she brought the Mika tribe to Verdurous Forest following the instructions from god. Listen to what {C=0xFF00863C/}Shaman Naoi{C=0xFF4D0D08/}'s has to say.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Syamalky

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll - Syamalky

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Last night, Naoi dreamed about you, {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. She dreamed that you would go to {C=0xFF016295/}Pinecone Knoll{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and enter Verdurous Forest safely following the forest's guide. The only way to enter Verdurous Forest is being blocked by woodmen Burnaun, so it is difficult to enter right now. Meet {C=0xFF00863C/}Syamalky{C=0xFF4D0D08/} who has been observing them woodmen at {C=0xFF016295/}Pinecone Knoll{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 30 Agnee

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll - Syamalky

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Syamalky's dream is to be the best hunter, he hopes to achieve this by following Parmir, who has been a hero for the Mika Tribe for over a thousand years. Syamalky has asked you to compete and see who is fastest to kill Agnee. Kill 30 Agnee at Pinecone Knoll.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Shaman Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll - Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Orhah is heading to where the woodmen are. Syamalky has asked you to find here, there are not enough people protecting her. Find {C=0xFF00863C/}Shaman Orhah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Pinecone Knoll{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and talk to her.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 30 Violent woodmen

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll - Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
According to Orhah the entrance to Verdurous Forest is blocked with an ancient magic shield. Only selected people can enter. So Woodman Burnaun is following orders from the Black Witch to cut a path through the trees to Verdurous Forest from {C=0xFF016295/}Pinecone Knoll{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to make a way to access Verdurous Forest. {C=0xFF00863C/}Shaman Orhah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} wants you to kill 30 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Violent woodmen{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Pinecone Knoll{C=0xFF4D0D08/}[Mission Mode].

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 1 Old Circular Saw Blades
{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll - Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Orhah thinks stealing the logging equipment from woodmen is more effective than killing them. Steal an {C=0xFFFF5917/}Old Circular Saw Blade{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from woodmen at {C=0xFF016295/}Pinecone Knoll{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for  {C=0xFF00863C/}Shaman Orhah{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Woodsman Paul Burnaun

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knolls - Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Orhah expects that all the woodsmen who are logging Verdurous Forest will stop and leave if we can kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Woodsman Paul Burnaun{C=0xFF4D0D08/} because they will lose their focus. Go to Pinecone Knoll [Arcade Mode F1] for {C=0xFF00863C/}Shaman,
Orhah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Woodsman Paul Burnaun{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll - Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Orhah is explaining the unfortunate history of the Mika tribe. A thousand years ago, a Knight sent by the Holy Empire massacred the Mika tribe. Shaman Charpira lead the Mika tribe to God's Sanctuary. Listen to {C=0xFF00863C/}Shaman Orhah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and he will tell you the full story.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Syamalky and Shangdor

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll - Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Orhah asked {C=0xFFFF5917/}Syamalky and Shangdor{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to conduct some reconnaissance on Paul Burnaun. Ask them what information they gathered while they were watching Paul Burnaun pass it on to {C=0xFF00863C/}Shaman Orhah{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Woodsman Paul Burnaun

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pinecone Knoll - Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Shaman Orhah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} wants you to make the first strike against the woodsmen group. Kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Woodsman Paul Burnaun{C=0xFF4D0D08/} who is preparing for battle at Pinecone Knoll[Scenario Mode (F5)].

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Hel Krouzer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gods' Sanctuary - Hel Krouzer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Black Witches apprentice, Mutisha,
is the one who sent lumber jacks to {C=0xFF016295/}Verdurous Forest{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Hel Krouzer, who protects {C=0xFFFF5917/}Verdurous Forest{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, is trying to track down Mutisha. Help him by travelling to {C=0xFFFF5917/}Verdurous Forest{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and talking with {C=0xFF00863C/}Mist Elf Hel Krouzer{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Pyrei

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gods' Sanctuary - Pyrei

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Naoi is impressed that the warrior she saw in her premonition was just like you, {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Naoi has asked you to find some help for the holy Kentarous who is protecting {C=0xFF016295/}Gods' Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Gods' Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and find {C=0xFF00863C/}Kentarous Pyrei{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to talk.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 30 Kentar

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gods' Sanctuary - Pyrei

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pyrei said there has been a civil war among the Kentar at {C=0xFF016295/}Gods' Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} since Mutisha's appearance. Even the cursed Kentar wants to take Pyrei...
Kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Kentar{C=0xFF4D0D08/} who are wandering at {C=0xFF016295/}Gods' Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Kentar Pyrei{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Keiron's Crossbow

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gods' Sanctuary - Pyrei

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pyrei said Kentar leader, Kentarous used to be a brave and great leader. But it seems he has lost all sense, he has been cursed by Mutisha. Pyrei has promised to tell you more details after you help him to get back his lost weapon from {C=0xFF016295/}Gods' Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Kill monsters at {C=0xFF016295/}Gods' Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} until you find {C=0xFFFF5917/}Keiron's crossbow{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and deliver it to {C=0xFF00863C/}Kentar Pyrei{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Karous

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gods' Sanctuary - Pyrei

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pyrei told you that Mutisha's intends to destroy Kundara's shield at Gods' Sanctuary. He warns you that as long as Hel Krouzer holds the ring which can disable but if that was to ever change he doesn't want to image what would happen. {C=0xFF00863C/}Kantarous Pyrei{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has requested you go to {C=0xFF016295/}Gods' Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Karous{C=0xFF4D0D08/} who's soul is under Mutisha's control.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Clear Gods' Sanctuary [Scenario Mode (F5)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gods' Sanctuary - Pyrei

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pyrei thinks he is safe from Mutisha's cursed magic as he has been excluded from the main group because of his bad temper. He was going to join the polluted Kentars because he felt so lonely but, {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/} gave Pyrei hope. For {C=0xFF00863C/}Kentar Pyrei{C=0xFF4D0D08/} kill the polluted Kanrarouss, Karous and {C=0xFFFF5917/}all other monsters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Gods' Sanctuary [Scenario Mode (F5)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Hel Krouzer at Gods' Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gods' Sanctuary - Hel Krouzer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pyrei said he will do anything to help you, he is in your debt after you helped him before. After he heard about {C=0xFF00863C/}Hel Krouzer{C=0xFF4D0D08/} he wrote a letter to persuade  {C=0xFF00863C/}Hel Krouzer{C=0xFF4D0D08/} himself. Go to Gods' Sanctuary, find {C=0xFF00863C/}Hel Krouzer{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and deliver {C=0xFFFF5917/}Pyrei's Letter{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain a Battle Pet Advancement Kit

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Amy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Pet Merchant Amy{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Ports of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/} suggests you promote Griffon to a battle pet as she thinks he is ready. If your Griffon becomes a battle pet then he will be very useful to you, he can help you pick up items, attack monsters for you, and breathe fire! You need a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Battle Pet Advancement Kit{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from Amy's shop to promote Griffon.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain a Battle Pet Advancement Kit

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Amy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Pet Merchant Amy{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/} suggests you promote Feilon to a battle pet as she thinks he is ready. If Feilon becomes a battle pet then he will be very useful to you, he can help you pick up items, attack monsters for you, and breathe fire! You need a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Battle Pet Advancement Kit{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from Amy's shop to promote Feilon.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk with Pablo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Pablo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Pablo said the {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Fairy Stone{C=0xFF4D0D08/} which was used by hero's thousands of years ago is required to prepare for the Black Dragon Lord Elga's revival. However, the {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Fairy Stone{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has disappeared thousands of years ago when Elga last disappeared. The only person who knows about this holy treasure is Mist Elf, Hel Krouzer who's protecting the Verdurous Forest. Arcanist
Pablo is hoping that you can meet Hel Krouzer at the Verdurous Forest, but a lot of trouble will be waiting for you.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Syari

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Syari

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Precious treasure of Earth has been detected at Verdurous Forest. Ochukoe wants you, {C=0xFF00863C/}%name%{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, to find out some information about Verdurous Forest and the Precious Treasure of Earth. Speak with {C=0xFF00863C/}Archpriest of Earth Syari{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} before making a trip to Verdurous Forest.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk with Hel Krouzer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Verdurous Forest - Hel Krouzer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hel Krouzer regrets that he has made things worse because of his stubbornness. If you cannot stop Mutisha who can now enter Kundara and control Aram freely, the {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Fairy Stone{C=0xFF4D0D08/} will go under the Witch Paris' control.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 100 monsters at Broken Mushroom Factory

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mushroom Town - Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Due to the current problems in Fungoid Village, Fungarf isn't interested in Hel Krouzer request. He is trying to rebuild the factory, but the monsters are disturbing the repair work. Kill 100 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Broken Mushroom Factory's monsters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Town Chief Fungarf{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Burlune

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mushroom Village - Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
According to Fungarf, he said the current accident happened because the Shroom Soldiers are trying to steal the temptation mushroom under the Black Witch's orders. He said does not know a lot about the Altar of the time but promised to tell you everything he knows if you can kill Burlune. Kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Monkey Leader, Burlune{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at Village of Slumber [Arcade Mode F1] for {C=0xFF00863C/}Town Cheif Fungarf{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain the Awakening Flute

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mushroom Village - Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Burlune who is hidden inside the Village of Slumber has stolen an {C=0xFFFF5917/}Awakening Flute{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from Fungarf. You can wake Bubo up by using this flute and obtain some important information about the Altar of the time. Kill monkey leader Burlune at the Village of Slumber [Scenario Mode (F5)] for {C=0xFF00863C/}Town Cheif Fungarf{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and return with the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Awakening Flute{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Clear Forgotten Village [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mushroom Village - Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungarf told you about the two thousand two hundred year old sage Bubo. He lives at the Forgotten Village. Clear {C=0xFF016295/}Forgotten Village [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to find Bubo.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Bubo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mushroom Village - Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungarf has asked you to kill Bubo while he is using the awakening flute.

Upon {C=0xFF00863C/}Town Cheif Fungarf's{C=0xFF4D0D08/} request, kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Sage Bubo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the Forgotten Village [Scenario Mode(F5)].

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Clear Land of Temptation [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mushroom Village - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Monadron came to Mushroom Village to collect a special mushroom but also has a strong interest in a monster known as Ice Handy at Frigid Canyon. 

Upon {C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron's{C=0xFF4D0D08/} request, clear {C=0xFF016295/}Land of Temptation [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain the Map of the truth

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mushroom Village - Fungarf

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungarf has said that finding Golem Pythanuth by chance is very fortunate for you. After Bubo, the only way to find the engraved map of the Altar of the time is by killing Golem Pythanuth.
Upon {C=0xFF00863C/}Town Cheif Fungarf's{C=0xFF4D0D08/} instructions, go to {C=0xFF016295/}Land of Temptation [Scenario Mode(F5)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and kill Golem Pythanuth to obtain the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Map of the truth{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver Pythanuth's Spirit Shard to Baron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ashmist Village - Baron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Fungarf thought the Spirit Shard from Pythanuth's remains used alchemy to hid the map of the truth. Fortunately, Baron in the nearby Ashmist Village specialises in alchemy, Fungarf suggests you go find him.

Following Fungarf's advice, go to {C=0xFF016295/}Ashmist Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, find {C=0xFF00863C/}Dark Magician Baron{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and deliver to him {C=0xFFFF5917/}Pythanuth's Spirit Shard{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to James

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ashmist Village - James

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dark Magician Baron who you met at {C=0xFF016295/}Ashmist Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} was invited by Count Van Cliff. Baron, who was late for the meeting for all of the alchemists and black magicians from all over the world was shocked when he came to the village because Count Van Cliff who sent all of the invitation letters died over 600 years ago. Go to find {C=0xFF00863C/}Real Estate Agent
James{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Ashmist Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Baron, who wants to know more details.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Baron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ashmist Village - Baron
{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Baron is very excited after he obtained information about the {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Altar of the time{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Pythanuth's Spirit Shard{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. The {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Altar of the time{C=0xFF4D0D08/}is the greatest ruin in history. It can provide people with power to control time after they have passed a test from the past, present and future areas of the ruin.

Go and speak to Baron about this.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Paris, the Black Witch

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Camp Steven - Colin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Colin has ordered everyone to kill Paris after he heard that {C=0xFF016295/}The top of Drakos Tower{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has been opened. Kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Paris, the Black Witch{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}The top of Drakos Tower{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Shaman Naoi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dragon Valley - Naoi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hel Krouzer cannot calm himself down now the black abyss has appeared. At the time it happened {C=0xFF00863C/}Mika tribe's Shaman Naoi{C=0xFF4D0D08/} would have been arriving at {C=0xFF016295/}Dragon Valley{C=0xFF4D0D08/} after she had a premonition, go and find her.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Shaman Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dragon Valley - Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Naoi said she is on the way to the Edge of the World after she had a new premonition. She has asked you to, go and find {C=0xFF00863C/}Shaman Orhah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Dragon Valley{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill each 30 Muchi and Boss Muchi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dragon Valley - Shangdor

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Shangdor{C=0xFF4D0D08/} said he followed Naoi here to protect Orhah while she heads toward the place she saw in her premonition. He looks like he is worrying about the shaman because there are a lot of monsters threatening shaman's safety. Kill 30 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Muchi{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and Boss {C=0xFFFF5917/}Muchi{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/} Dragon Valley{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Clear Dragon Valley [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dragon Valley - Orhah

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Orhah is trying to find where Elga's hiding place in Dragon Valley is located. However, she bumped into Demon while looking for traces of Naoi and Elga. The demon cursed her with a sentence of death. Orhah is preparing for the final battle with {C=0xFFFF5917/}Demon Peurogel{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Clear {C=0xFF016295/}Dragon Valley [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and find {C=0xFFFF5917/}Demon Peurogel{C=0xFF4D0D08/}'s location for {C=0xFF00863C/}the Shaman and Orhah{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Demon Prokell

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dragon Valley - Syamalky

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Syamalky was injured when he was killing the monsters at Dragon Valley for the Shaman's safety. Therefore the shaman asked him to go back his hometown for Syamalky and Shangdor's safety but, the brave young warriors from the Mika tribe decided to be together with the shaman until the end. Syamalky wants you to, kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Demon Prokell{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Dragon Valley [Scenario Mode(F5)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Hel Krouzer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Camp Steven - Hel Krouzer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Naoi said she found the mountain top where Elga's shriek came from in her premonition. She wants you to tell everyone at the expedition at Camp Steven... Go to find Hel Krouzer at Camp Steven and tell him this for Sharman, Naoi.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill 100 monsters at the Edge of the world

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Edge of the world - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mukapa is under a lot of pressure and needs you to kill the many spirits who are at {C=0xFF016295/}Edge of the world {C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Kill any 100 monsters at the {C=0xFF016295/}Edge of the world{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Temple Archpriest, Mukapa {C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Clear Edge of the world [Scenario Mode(F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Camp Steven - Colin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
A lot of soldiers have been deployed to the Edge of the world to find out where all of the spirits have been coming from, however, most of them have perished in battle. Only one thing was revealed during the investigation, and that is that the spirits are coming from the {C=0xFF016295/}Edge of the world [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. On behalf of {C=0xFF00863C/}Guard Captain, 
Colin{C=0xFF4D0D08/} go and investigate {C=0xFF016295/}Edge of the world [Scenario Mode(F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in more detail.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kill Carsharp

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ellora Camp - Hel Krouzer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hel Krouzer is angry about the fact that spirits are appearing at Dark Abyss because of Carsharp's dance. Be quick, the time we are taking to defeat Carsharp, the power we have for Elga's Expedition is weakening. Following {C=0xFF00863C/}Hel Krouzer{C=0xFF4D0D08/}'s instruction, go to {C=0xFF016295/}Edge of the world [Scenario Mode(F5)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and kill {C=0xFFFF5917/}Carsharp{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Purify Precious Treasure of Earth

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Precious Treasure of Earth

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Help stop the ancient Drakan's ghost called Akanai which was released from the Precious Treasure of Earth... lots of Drakan warriors have been heading to {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/} but most of them are getting wounded. Archpriest of Shadow Rue sacrificed herself to try and seal in Akanai, he used {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Garuda's Spell{C=0xFF4D0D08/} which has greatly reduced the pollution level of the precious treasure. For all the sacrificed priests and warriors, go to {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, find the precious treasure and purify it. All those who have perished rest in peace.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Akanai's Shadow Essence

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Danku

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
A mysterious old man called {C=0xFF00863C/}Danku{C=0xFF4D0D08/} said he needs {C=0xFFFF0000/}Akanai's Shadow Essence{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Find Akanai at {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, Akanai has the Shadow Essence and will certainly not let you have it while he is still living. Kill Akanai, obtain the Shadow Essence and take it to {C=0xFF00863C/}Danku{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Akanai's Shadow Essence

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Danku

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
A mysterious old man called {C=0xFF00863C/}Danku{C=0xFF4D0D08/} said he needs {C=0xFFFF0000/}Akanai's Shadow Essence{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Find Akanai at {C=0xFF016295/}Akia Cave{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, Akanai has the Shadow Essence and will certainly not let you have it while he is still living. Kill Akanai, obtain the Shadow Essence and take it to {C=0xFF00863C/}Danku{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Battle Pet Advancement Kit

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Amy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You need a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Battle Pet Advancement Kit{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to proceed with the 1st class promotion for your riding pet. You can easily get a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Battle Pet Advancement Kit{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFF00863C/}Pet Merchant Amy's{C=0xFF4D0D08/} shop.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tianshan Snow Lotus

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Syari

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You need a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Tianshan Snow Lotus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to proceed with 2nd class promotion for riding pet. You can easily get a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Tianshan Snow Lotus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from a {C=0xFF00863C/}Potion Merchant{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in Port of the Winds in exchange for gold. It's very expensive though.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk with Mukapa at Black Claw Nest Outpost

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
At Black Claw Nest Outpost, Hel Krouzer says that we have to cooperate to fight Elga.
{C=0xFF00863C/}Temple archpriest Mukapa{C=0xFF4D0D08/} has scouted Black Claw Nest area. Go talk to Mukapa.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gain info from Maruphu and Rophu

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mukapa asked to gain info on Black Claw Nest from the two scouts Maruphu and Rophu. Ask {C=0xFF00863C/}Maruphu and Rophu{C=0xFF4D0D08/} about what they know of Black Claw Nest.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Black Dragon Lord Elga

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Colin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Now the time has come. Human and Drakan have assembled beneath Origin. Invade Black Claw Nest with your unstoppable force. The goal is to immediately defeat {C=0xFFFF0000/}Black Dragon Lord Elga{C=0xFF4D0D08/} who is waiting for his revival.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring a piece of Black Claw

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Baron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Elga has appeared in Black Claw Nest due to the twisted space time Grantnoir created.
{C=0xFF00863C/}Dark Magician Baron{C=0xFF4D0D08/} asked you to defeat Elga and bring him a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Piece of Black Claw{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in return for the {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Cape of Black Dragon Lord Recipe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Piece of Black Claw

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Rudaella

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Rudaella{C=0xFF4D0D08/} wants to make a necklace using {C=0xFFFF0000/}Piece of Black Claw{C=0xFF4D0D08/} which can be obtained after defeating Elga. Bring her a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Piece of Black Claw{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get a Helmet of Black Dragon Lord Recipe{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in return.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Piece of Black Claw

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Elga's still roams Black Claw Nest. {C=0xFF00863C/}Temple archpriest Mukapa{C=0xFF4D0D08/} asked you to defeat Black Dragon Lord Elga and bring {C=0xFFFF0000/}Piece of Black Claw{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. He will reward you with the {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Top of Black Dragon Lord Recipe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Piece of Black Claw

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Colin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Colin seems to have a Black Dragon Lord Recipe. The High magicians of Dragon Fellowships says they want to investigate the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Piece of Black Claw{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Defeat Elga and bring {C=0xFFFF5917/}Piece of Black Claw{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to {C=0xFF00863C/}Captain Colin{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. {C=0xFF00863C/}Captain Colin{C=0xFF4D0D08/} will give you a {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Black Dragon Lord Bottom recipe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Piece of Black Claw

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Mohamo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mohamo would like to have a Piece of Black Claw as a souvenir for visiting the Black Claw Nest. Let's give Mist Elf Mohamo the Piece of Black Claw that can be obtained by defeating Elga. You can receive a {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Black Dragon Lord Shoulder Recipe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Piece of Black Claw

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Captain Thomas{C=0xFF4D0D08/} would like to have a piece of Black Claw to raise the soldier's spirits. Any one who brings the Black Claw will be rewarded with {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Black Dragon Lord Gloves recipe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Lets defeat Elga and bring a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Piece of Black Claw{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to captain Thomas.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Piece of Black Claw

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Hoffman

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Captain Hoffman{C=0xFF4D0D08/} heard about the bet that Thomas has, so he is opening a competition. Any one who brings him a piece of Black Claw will be given a Black Dragon Lord shoes recipe. Defeat Elga and bring {C=0xFFFF5917/}Piece of Black Claw{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to {C=0xFF00863C/}Captain Hoffman{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and you will be given the {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Black Dragon Lord Shoes Recipe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Piece of Black Claw

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Black Claw Nest Outpost - Tatanka

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Blacksmith Tatanka{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is out at the Black Claw Nest. She has {C=0xFFA71FC9/}Black Dragon Lord Weapon Recipe{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and is willing to trade for a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Piece of Black Claw{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, that can be obtained by defeating Elga at the Black Claw Nest.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to ChiChai

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Vartika Hill - ChiChai

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Because it's been such a long time since Croquis has seen you, Croquis wants to give you a special 'long time no see' gift! Talk to Trade Merchant {C=0xFF00863C/}ChiChai{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, they are good friends and Croquis has arranged for you to collect the gift from him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 1 Prune Pouch

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Vartika Hill - ChiChai

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Master Chief wannabe ChiChai set out on a long journey with Croquis to collect the best food ingredients from all over Dragotaka. Unfortunately Croquis has been busy with secret missions and ChiChai has been left to continue alone. Help ChiChai by defeating {C=0xFFFF5917/}Hill Gnolls{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Vartika Hill{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Prune Pouch{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for ChiChai.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Dragon Liquor

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Vartika Hill - ChiChai

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Trade Merchant ChiChai{C=0xFF4D0D08/} still has more ingredients to collect in Vartika Hill. He wants some Dragon Liquor made from a Dragon Teardrop to recreate one of his mum's dishes.
Defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Donply{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Vartika Hill Mission Map [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get some {C=0xFFFF5917/}Dragon Liquor{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for ChiChai.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Flame Scouts

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Vartika Hill - Croquis

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Croquis travelled to {C=0xFF016295/}Vartika Hill{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to find a Dragon Egg. The Vargons and Hill Gnolls have never been very close in the past but recently they have been up to something together. Croquis is interested in what they are up to and wants your help to identify what they are after.
For {C=0xFF00863C/}Drakan Adventurer Croquis{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, defeat 30 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Flame Scouts{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Vartika Hill{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Donply

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Vartika Hill - Croquis

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Once Croquis heard that ChiChai got some Dragon Liquor made from the teardrop of a Dragon he instantly came to the conclusion that the Dragon Egg must be at the same place the teardrop was found.
Defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Donply{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}Vartika Hill Mission Map [Hero Quest Mode(F5)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and return with the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Dragon Egg{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for {C=0xFF00863C/}Drakan Adventurer Croquis{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Drake Gorge and Florence Gorge

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Mohamo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mohamo has come to deliver the ancient Boost Backpack, a great treasure. Mohamo is fed up of having to run errands for other species and has arrived in a bad mood and say she is not going to deliver the ancient treasure.
Defeat  {C=0xFFFF5917/}Drake Gorge and Florence Gorge{C=0xFF4D0D08/} who attacked {C=0xFF00863C/}Mist Elf Mohamo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in order to make her feel better.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Backpack Upgrade Kit

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Mohamo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Based on the ancient books Mohamo has been reading, Mohamo believes that it's possible to upgrade the Boost Backpack using a Backpack Upgrade Kit. The clues she has collected indicate that Cetirus in Red Fox Delta may have a Backpack Upgrade kit but it wont be an easy battle. Defeat Cetirus to obtain a Backpack Upgrade Kit.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Syamalky

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Mohamo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mohamo has asked you to deliver Rugor's message to {C=0xFF00863C/}Syamalky in Banshi Gorge{C=0xFF4D0D08/} while the Boost Backpack is being upgraded. Because Rugor found Parmir's arrowhead it would be best if Syamalky comes back to the village. By the time you return to Mohamo after delivering the message the upgraded Boost Backpack should be ready to pickup.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk with Princecia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Princecia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Duke Monadron is famous for collecting strange stuff. Now he is searching for {C=0xFF00863C/}Princess Candidate Princecia{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. He has been asking the locals to help find her and pass on the message that he wants her to return to the palace.
Why has Princecia come to Banshi Gorge?
Locate {C=0xFF00863C/}Princecia{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and pass on the message.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Princecia came here to try and convince Jack and Jess to stop helping Duke Monadron who is up to no good. But with the Duke on her tail and everyone looking for her she has asked you to persuade Jess on her behalf.
{C=0xFF00863C/}Jess{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is with Duke Monadron in Banshi Gorge right now, go and talk to him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jack says Duke Monadron has set Jess up and made him sign an unfair contract. Jack is worries that his brother may loose his life as he is being forced to steal precious treasures from the dangerous Hydron Core. 
Jack would like you to try to persuade {C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron in Banshi Gorge{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to let Jess go.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain an Armoured Golem's Steel Horn

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/} says his contract with Jess is not unreasonable, but it seems he is holding a grudge against Jack for stealing the treasure he was desperately after.
You can cancel Jess' contact with Duke Monadron by completing his three wishes.
His first wish is for you to bring him an {C=0xFFFF5917/}Armoured Golem's Steel Horn{C=0xFF4D0D08/} by defeating the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Armoured Golem{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Fox Delta{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Armoured Barrel's steel tail

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is willing to cancel the contract he made with Jess upon if you bring him three special items. The second item he has requested is {C=0xFFFF5917/}Armoured Barrel's Steel Tail{C=0xFF4D0D08/} that can be obtained after defeating {C=0xFFFF5917/}Armoured Golem in Red Fox Delta{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Armoured Kampaling's Steel Jaw

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is willing to cancel the contract he made with Jess upon if you bring him three special items. The third item he has requested is {C=0xFFFF5917/}Armoured Kampaling's Steel Jaw{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. {C=0xFFFF5917/}Armoured Kampaling{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is in {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Fox Delta{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain a Skystone

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Monadron

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
{C=0xFF00863C/}Duke Monadron{C=0xFF4D0D08/} asked for the three special items so he could obtain a piece of Skystone from {C=0xFF016295/}Hydron Core{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the deepest part of Red Fox Delta. Unfortunately the people Monadron sent were killed by Cetirus once they entered Hydron Core.
The Duke has asked you to defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Cetirus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and obtain a piece of {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skystone{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to the Unknown Hunter

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Unknown Hunter

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Princecia thinks she saw Parmir, one of the heroes from a thousand years ago she saw through the great magic at the Citadel of Torment. Since Princecia cannot go herself because of Duke Monadron's men searching for her visit the {C=0xFF00863C/}Unknown Hunter{C=0xFF4D0D08/} that resembles Parmir and see what you can find out.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Syamalky

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Syamalky

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Unknown Hunter is suffering from amnesia and really isn't sure who she is. Return to her with a person who knows Parmir very well and prove to her who she is. Visit Parmir's biggest fan, {C=0xFF00863C/}Syamalky{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF00863C/}Banshi Gorge{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and ask for his help.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver Syamalky's Parchment

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Unknown Hunter


{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Syamalky, Parmir's biggest fan is excited of the news that Parmir has come back alive. She has drawn Parmir's Mark that she saw engraved on Parmir's arrowhead Rugor kept.
Take {C=0xFFFF5917/}Syamalky's Parchment{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to the {C=0xFF00863C/}Unknown Hunter{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to help her regain her memory.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Investigate Mysterious Junk

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Mysterious Junk

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
To show their appreciation for your help in saving Jess from Duke Monadron's unfair contract, Jack wants to give you some {C=0xFF00863C/}Mysterious Clock{C=0xFF4D0D08/} they brought back from Red Fox Delta.
The junk doesn't look like it's working...

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Tarquin Liquid

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Mysterious Junk

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
While investigating the junk Jack gave you, you placed your hand on its glowing pattern and the junk began to steam, whizz and whirr.
The {C=0xFF00863C/}Mysterious Junk{C=0xFF4D0D08/} complained about a low battery and asked for some {C=0xFFFF5917/}Tarquin Liquid{C=0xFF4D0D08/} before it shutdown. It said you should be able to get some from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Cetirus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in Red Fox Delta.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to the Mysterious Junk

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Mysterious Junk

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Mysterious Junk finally introduced itself to you as Kyoneske, it came here to save the word from the oncoming darkness and restore the world to balance.
It wouldn't hurt to listen to the {C=0xFF00863C/}Mysterious Junk's{C=0xFF4D0D08/} story.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to the Unknown Hunter

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Unknown Hunter

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kyoneske says that it pulled the five heroes out of the Dark Abyss because they can control the Spiritual Protection Stones. Unfortunately while they were in the Dark Abyss they have lost their memories.
Now Kyoneske knows Parmir is near it has asked you to deliver its message to Parmir, the {C=0xFF00863C/}Unknown Hunter{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Jack

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banshi Gorge - Jack

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
While listening to Kyoneske's story Jess went crazy when he heard the word Great Magic... He is now stating that Kyoneske belongs to him and he is going to sell it once he gets back to the village.
Talk to his brother, {C=0xFF00863C/}Jack{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Jack in the Village of Ash Mist 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Village of Ash Mist - Jack

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jack is heading to the Village of Ash Mist with his brother Jess. He has invited you to visit him next time you are passing through.
Go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Village of Ash Mist{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and meet Jack.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Chief Scientist Noel

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Noel

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Noel has been inspired by his old Colleague, Dr Farrell's, research work.
Noel has begun conducting his own research into the Socket Cards containing Spirit Shards to help his Guardian Tower research. Talk to {C=0xFF00863C/}Chief Scientist Noel{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to find out more.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Extract Lv2. Fire Element

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Noel

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Chief Scientist Noel says only a few chosen people have the ability to handle the energy of the spirits and are able to extract the elements from the Spirit Shards.  Extract a {C=0xFFFF0000/}Lv2. Fire Element{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from a Lv2. Fire Spirit Shard and hand it over to {C=0xFF00863C/}Chief Scientist Noel{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Max

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Max

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Chief Scientist Noel has been researching the Socket Cards which allow you to apply the Elements from Spirit Shards to equipment.
Noel has asked {C=0xFF00863C/}Production Master Max{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to develop Socket Card for him. Find out how the creation of the card is progressing by speaking to Max.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver the Experimental Socket Card Box

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Noel

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Skilful Max has developed a Experimental Socket Card Box for Chief Scientist Noel. Production Master Max has asked you to deliver the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Experimental Socket Card Box{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to {C=0xFF00863C/}Chief Scientist Noel{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Libra{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Don't keep the good scientist waiting!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver the Spiritual Card Socket Adapter to Blacksmith Anders

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Anders

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Once the adapter is attached it becomes possible at apply the power of the element inside the Socket Card to equipment. Chief Scientist Noel would like you to go to {C=0xFF016295/}Libra{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and deliver the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spiritual Card Socket Adapter{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to {C=0xFF00863C/}Blacksmith Anders{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for upgrades.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver Socketed Helmet

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Libra - Noel

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Blacksmith Anders has created a socket on a Helmet as Noel requested. Anders would like you to deliver the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Socketed Helmet{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to {C=0xFF00863C/}Chief Scientist Noel{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Libra{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak with great magician Gwen

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Kazeura Village - Gwen

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
After completing the experiment with Chief Scientist Noel, the greatest magician, Gwen Rubin appeared at Kazeura Village. Gwen will take worthy adventurers to the Guardians' Dungeon where the Spirit Shards can be found. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Kazeura Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and talk to {C=0xFF00863C/}Great Magician Gwen{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 15 Jelly and 15 Red Jelly from Nautilus Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - James

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
James's customers are making requests he is having difficulty fulfilling.
James values his customers highly and wants to keep their loyalty so has asked you to defeat 15 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Jelly{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Jelly{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Nautilus Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/} clearing the way to build a Themed Spooky Restaurant for his customers.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Shark Deckhand Teeth in Nautilus Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - James

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
James's customer requires 10 Shark Deckhand Teeth, to protect James's rapport with his customer bring him 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhand Teeth{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFF016295/}Nautilus Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Shark Pirates at Nautilus Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - James

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
James's customer keeps making strange requests. The customer has asked James to reduce the number of Shark Pirates at Nautilus Port, he fears it may affect the success of his restaurant.
Help James out with his headache, defeat 30 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Nautilus Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Achieve a 200 Combos in Nautilus Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Cyndi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Cyndi thinks you are slow. She says if you are as fast as you think you are you should be able to achieve a 200 Combo in Nautilus Port.
Prove yourself to Cyndi by accepting her challenge and achieving a {C=0xFFFF5917/}200 Combo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Nautilus Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 40 Monsters at Nautilus Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Cyndi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Cyndi says being fast is not enough, you need strength before you can be recognised for abilities. Prove your strength to Cyndi by defeating {C=0xFFFF5917/}40 Monsters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Nautilus Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Blue Jelly at Jigsaw Pincers Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Bartie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bartie is angry that so many people are coming to Port of the Winds dreaming of becoming a hero. Prove to Bartie you are different, better, than the others by going to {C=0xFF016295/}Jigsaw Pincers Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeating {C=0xFFFF5917/}Blue Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Crabby Shells from Crabbies in Jigsaw Pincers Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Edeline

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Chanpio has an important meditation session today, but he's anxious about something and is having trouble trying to focus. Help Chanpio out by collecting {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Crabby Shells{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Jigsaw Pincers Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Take the collected shells to {C=0xFF00863C/}Edeline{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Chanpio in Port of the Winds

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Chanpio

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Edeline believes that the Crabby Shells are the culprit for the modification of the potion, perhaps they have been spoilt by a rouge element. If anyone drank the potion, it would make the persons mind more distracted.
Convey Edeline's message to {C=0xFF00863C/}Chanpio{C=0xFF4D0D08/} who's waiting for the potion.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Razor Crabbies in Jigsaw Pincers Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Chanpio

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Chanpio knows what caused the alteration to the Crabby Shells. Recently the Razor Crabby have been changed by someone and their close proximity to the Crabbies have caused them to be infected too.
Separating the Crabbies from the Razor Crabbies should allow them to return to normal.
Defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Razor Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Jigsaw Pincers Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 15 Blue Shark Fins from Shark Pirates and Shark Deckhands at Decker Shark Piers

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Bartie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bartie is worried about his summoned monsters, they have lost their appetite and are getting weaker day by day. Bartie says a delicacy of the port, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Blue Shark Fins{C=0xFF4D0D08/} will help the monsters get well again.
Help Bartie create a tasty broth for his monsters by obtaining {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Blue Shark Fins{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Achieve a 250 Combo at Decker Shark Piers

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Chanpio

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Chanpio is disappointed that not many people are practicing the art of Combos, one of the fighters most elegant arts.
Let him see that there are still many people who enjoy making combos. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Decker Shark Piers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and achieve a {C=0xFFFF5917/}250 Combo{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Jelly and Red Jelly at Decker Shark Piers

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mukapa is concerned about the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} because of their recent violence against people passing through the Decker Shark Piers. They are shooting a deadly poison at people, this problem has to be dealt with swiftly. Defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Jellies and Red Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to make the {C=0xFF016295/}Decker Shark Piers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} safe again.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 15 Mulosca Skins at Nautilus Port give them to Daisy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Daisy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
James's father has terrible muscular pains, James has pain too but he thinks his fathers is much worse and wants to make him a {C=0xFFFF5917/}Muscular Pain Relief Potion{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
Collect {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Mulosca Skins{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, the main ingredient for the potion, from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Nautilus Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
When you have them take them to {C=0xFF00863C/}Daisy{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/}

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver the Pain Relief Potion to Jeremy in Port of the Winds

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Jeremy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Daisy used the Mulosca Skins you collected for James to create the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Muscular Pain Relief Potion{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
Deliver the potion to {C=0xFF00863C/}Jeremy{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/} so he doesn't have to suffer from his muscular pain anymore.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Crabby Monsters at the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Rudolph

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rudolph was picked on by a swarm of Crabbies while relaxing at the Bearded Whale Coast. Rudolph is having nightmares about the incident and cannot sleep well, give them some pay back by defeating {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gather 10 Yellow Stars from the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Rudolph

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rudolph likes colleting star shaped things and really wants some Yellow Stars to add to his collection. He has found out that the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Lolos{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} have them. Gather 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Yellow Stars{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Rudolph.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Shark Pirates in the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Davy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
A few days ago some {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} came to Davy and demanded he created weapons for them for free. Davy doesn't want to help the Sharks, they lack morals and just want to use them for piracy. For the sake of Justice defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to ensure they don't return.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Reclaim 15 Harpoon Tips from the Shark Deckhands in the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Davy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Davy trusted one of the Shark Deckhands claim that he wanted to go leave his pirating ways and become a fisherman. Davy gave him 15 Harpoon Tips on credit and only expected some of the Shark Deckhands catch in return.
The Shark Deckhand never returned to Davy and he has heard they are now using Harpoons to commit piracy. Get the {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Harpoon Tips{C=0xFF4D0D08/} back from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhand{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Davy.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Achieve a 300 Combo in the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Chanpio

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Chanpio is whining that no one can do a decent combo in the Bearded Whale Coast. While whining to you he challenged you to complete the combo yourself to prove it's possible. Show your excellent skills to Chanpio and achieve a {C=0xFFFF5917/}300 Combo{C=0xFF4D0D08/}  in the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 40 monsters in the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Daisy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Daisy is upset because she cannot visit the Bearded Whale Coast anymore because of all the monsters. People used to flock to the coast to enjoy the warm sand and splash in the surf but the place is deserted these days. Comfort Daisy by defeating {C=0xFFFF5917/}40 Monsters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to make it safe for tourists again.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 15 Shark Pirates at the Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode(F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Daisy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Daisy is mad at the Shark Pirates. They came to her store and smashed all of her potions, they are all ruined. Help Daisy get revenge on them. Defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode(F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. They are good at hiding so you should check a mission with more than 2 maps, you might need to try more than once.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 15  Red Jelly monsters at the Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode(F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Ersil

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ersil says the Red Jelly monsters around the coast are leaving a slimey residue before they run away. He keeps having to clean up the coast after them and it's giving him a lot of back trouble even though he's just a young boy.
Defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}40 Red Jelly{C=0xFF4D0D08/} monsters in the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode(F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
They are good at hiding so you should check a mission with more than 2 maps, you might need to try more than once.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get back Mum's Thing from the Shark Pirates in the Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode (F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Ersil

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ersil is worried because the Shark Pirates at the Bearded Whale Coast snatched back one of his Mum's Things he borrowed claiming it belonged to their boss.
It's some kind of  Eye Patch. Go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode (F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get back {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mum's Thing{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
They are good at hiding so you should check a mission with more than 2 maps, you might need to try more than once.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast  [Arcade Mode F1] - Get Captain Hookah's hat

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Cyndi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Cyndi doesn't like Captain Hookah because he is giving thieves a bad name... Punish him for her by stealing {C=0xFFFF5917/}Captain Hookah's Hat{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 15 Barrel Bones and 15 Broken Barrel Bones in the City Hall Sewer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Walter

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Walter has been receiving many report of clattering sounds coming from the City Hall Sewer. Help Walter and the locals out by going down into the {C=0xFF016295/}City Hall Sewers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeating {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Barrel Bones{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Broken Barrel Bones{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Fabric bunches from Spiked Mace Mummy monsters in the City Hall Sewer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Florence

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Florence is preparing some pieces for a local fashion contest but is worried that she won't have enough fabric to finish her work! Florence reckons the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spiked Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}City Hall Sewer{C=0xFF4D0D08/} should have plenty of Fabric Bunches on them. Try and collect {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Fabric Bunches{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 10 Wolf Monsters in the City Hall Sewer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Evan

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Evan is worried about some {C=0xFFFF5917/}Wolf Monsters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} that have been appearing in the village. They have some kind of mad wolf disease, it's a threat to everyone that lives in Port of the Winds.
Help Evan out by slaying {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Wolf Monsters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} with this terrible disease down in the {C=0xFF016295/}City Hall Sewer{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get the Love Contract back from Steamed Juju in the City Hall Sewer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Rony

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rony got a little bit too merry the other night and was tricked into signing Steamed Juju's Love Contract. To save Rony from a life of being Steamed Juju's pet get back the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Love Contract{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Steamed Juju{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}City Hall Sewer{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Chief Cook Kakanu in the City Hall Sewer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Rudolph

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rudolph met Chief Cook Kakanu while he was travelling Dragotaka training to become a master chef. Rudolph puts great love, care and attention into his food but Kakanu only cares about selling his food, and not about its safety or freshness. He is a threat to the village, many people who eat his food get sick. Defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Chief Cook Kakanu{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}City Hall Sewer{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and put Rudolph's mind at rest.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 15 Oak Tree Barrels from Barrel Bones and Broken Barrel Bones in the City Hall Sewer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Rudolph

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rudolph wants to brew his drinks in his families traditional way to give them a much better taste than they do now. Rudolph has located a source of {C=0xFFFF5917/}Oak Tree Barrels{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}City Hall Sewer{C=0xFF4D0D08/} but they all contain {C=0xFFFF5917/}Barrel Bones{C=0xFF4D0D08/} or {C=0xFF4D0D08/}Broken Barrel Bones.
Clear out and return with {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Oak Tree Barrels{C=0xFF4D0D08/} so you may taste Rudolph's tasty brew.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Spiked Mace Mummies at the City Hall Sewer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Cyndi

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
While on a stroll at night through the village Cyndi was passing by the City Hall Sewers when she saw something horrible. Cyndi is terrified of ghosts, it almost gave her a heart attack. Help Cyndi calm down and remove her fear of going out at night by defeating {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Spiked Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}City Hall Sewer{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Take back the Stolen Helmet from Franken Doju in the City Hall Sewer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Vincent

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Vincent is trying to get back Steven Jr's Helmet which was stolen from an exhibition at the last national anniversary by Doju. The Helmet was being kept my Steven Jr as a trophy from winning a past war.
Vincent would appreciate it if you could claim back the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Stolen Helmet{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Franken Doju{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. He has received a few reports that he can be found down in the {C=0xFF016295/}City Hall Sewer{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 8 bananas from the Porky monsters in the City Hall Sewer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Daisy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Daisy's Special Bananas she just bought especially for her store have been stolen by the Porky Monsters. Daisy is going to close her shop in Port of the Winds and move to another village because she is so angry with all of the recent incidents. Go down into the {C=0xFF016295/}City Hall Sewer{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get back {C=0xFFFF5917/}9 Special Bananas{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Porkies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 10 Five Spice from Boombooms in the City Hall Sewer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Daisy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Daisy has obtained some information about the legendary seasoning {C=0xFFFF5917/}Five Spice{C=0xFF4D0D08/} necessary to make the dishes with the most amazing flavour.
According to Daisy the special component of the seasoning comes from monsters called Boombooms. It's really hard to find the right ones exactly. Thankfully Daisy heard that some people saw these special type of {C=0xFFFF5917/}Boomboom{C=0xFF4D0D08/} monsters in the {C=0xFF016295/}City Hall Sewer{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Go down there and get {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Five Spice{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from them.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 15 Shark Deckhands and 15 Shark Pirates at the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Davy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Davy once trained to become a warrior himself. The problems over at the Bearded Whale Coast have therefore interested him and provoked him to do something to stop it. Help Davy calm down by slaying {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 30 Starry Lulu and Starry Lolo at the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Davy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Davy says the hardest battles are the ones where you have to use your endurance to fight many monsters for a long time. Davy wants you to experience this in your training, head to the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Starry Lolo{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. You better keep your wits about you or you'll get surrounded.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 10 Red Jellies, 10 Jellies and 10 Crabby in [Arcade Mode(F1)] at the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Davy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
To complete your training Davy wants you to experience one of the most important things he learnt during his time as a Warrior. By facing 3 different monsters at once you will need to learn how to observe them and identify their weaknesses. Only through this will you learn how to survive the most difficult battles you will face.
Davy wants you to slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Red Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode(F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} .
They are good at hiding so you should check a mission with more than 2 maps, you might need to try more than once.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 15 Fish from Shark Pirates and Shark Deckhands at the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Primo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Ersil is dreaming of becoming the greatest fisherman in all of Dragotaka. He challenged Primo in the Bearded Whale Coast to see who could catch the most fish but Shark Pirates and Shark Deckhands stole Ersil's fine catch.
Help Ersil prove he won the contest with Primo by getting back the {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Fish{C=0xFF4D0D08/} he caught from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring back 15 Lunch Fish taken by the Sharks from Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Primo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Sharks at the Bearded Whale Coast sniffed out and stole Primo's tasty lunch he created. He is very sad because he needs a good meal to boost his strength. Help out Primo by going to the {C=0xFF016295}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and bring him back {C=0xFFFF5917}15 Lunch Fish{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the sharks.
They are good at hiding so you should check a mission with different difficulties and you might also need to try more than once.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Captain Hookah in the Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Primo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Primo was enjoying a nice afternoons fishing when Captain Hookah decided to visit him. He saw how much fun he was having and asked to use his fishing rod to try it out. He started fishing but soon became impatient and angry and snapped Primo's fishing rod clean in half! Cheer Primo up by teaching {C=0xFFFF5917/}Captain Hookah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} a lesson.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 20 Crabby Shells from the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Leo wants to give a small present to someone special but he cannot think of a good present to give. He recently found out that Crabby Soup is really good for your health so he has decided to cook a healthy dish to give to them as a gift.
Leo requires {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Crabby Shells{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for the soup, they can be found at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Give him a hand in making someone feel special.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 15 Shark Tails from Shark Pirates and shark Deckhand at the Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Daisy tried Leo's dish but thought there was something missing, she suggested the food wasn't special enough. To make Leo's meal more special he would like to make it with Shark Tails.
Help Leo with his cooking by going to the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and slaying {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Shark Tails{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from them.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 20 Special Spice from the Starry LuLu at the Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode(F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Leo made a tasty dish using the Crabby Shells and the Shark Tails you collected and took the dish to Rudolph, the ports best cook, but he said it wasn't as good as it could be.
Rudolph suggested using a Special Spice from Starry Lulus would make the dish taste even better.
Go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode(F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and return with {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Special Spice{C=0xFF4D0D08/} collected from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lulus{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
Not all Starry Lulus have the Spice so you should try many different maps.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 1 Seaweed from Captain Hookah at the Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Leo shared the meal he created with Grandpa James since has similar tastes to his Grandpa Jeremy, the person he wants to give his meal as a present to. James said there was just one thing missing from the meal, seafood dishes created with Seaweed will bring joy to your taste buds, he said. Bring back some {C=0xFFFF5917}Seaweed{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Leo by defeating {C=0xFFFF5917}Captain Hookah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 20 Blue Jelly Extract from Blue Jellies at the Jigsaw Pincers Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Bartie

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bartie is worried that his summoned creature have dry skin after being in so many battles. Cindy says Blue Jelly Extract is great for hydrating skin but the extract can only be obtained from Blue Jellies at the Jigsaw Pincers Coast. Improve the friendship between Humans and Drakan by going to the {C=0xFF016295/}Jigsaw Pincers Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and obtaining {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Blue Jelly Extracts{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Blue Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 40 Blue Jellies at the Jigsaw Pincers Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mukapa has learned about some strange things which are going on a the Jigsaw Pincers Coast with the Blue Jellies. Mukapa claims that the Blue Jellies are sending strange signals from their antenna, it causes all the monsters in the area to group together. They are causing a threat to the nearby Port of the Winds. Slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}40 Blue Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Jigsaw Pincers Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Crabby and 20 Razor Crabby.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Chanpio

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Chanpio could not find any potion to calm her down, she thinks her training is suffering because she cannot stop thinking about it. To help stop her thinking about potions to calm her down she needs help to slay some Crabbies.
Slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Razor Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, the Crabby have infected, at the {C=0xFF016295/}Jigsaw Pincers Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/}  so Chanpio can concentrate on her training.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Conversation with Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Leo has lost something Jess trusted him with. He is worried that if Jess finds out then he will never want to see him ever again.
Help Leo out go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and speak to {C=0xFFFF5917/}Jess{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 10 Crabbies and 10 Starry Lulu at the Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jess wants one hundred million gold to replace the stuff Leo lost. After hearing that you do not have even nearly enough Jess has asked you to complete some physical labour instead. He would like to know how strong you actually are before he gives you the laborious task.
Prove your ability to Jess by slaying {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
They are good at hiding so you should check many different maps.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Shark Pirates and 20 Jellies at the Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jess is putting your last success down to luck and wants to see more proof that you are ready for the Physical Labour he is about to give you.
He wants you to slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2){C=0xFF4D0D08/} so he is sure you are capable.
They are good at hiding so you should check many different maps.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Locked Boxes from Shark Deckhands at the Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jess is excited that the real work can begin, it's something secret.
He says that the Shark Deckhands have stolen some kind of special Locked Boxes. If he could get some of them he would be able to calm down a bit.
Calm Jess down by collecting {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Locked Boxes{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Grab Captain Hookah's Secret Key from the Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Now is the opportunity to get Jess to forgive Leo. Jess has sources which have informed him Captain Hookah carries a Secret Key which opens the locked boxes. It's a difficult task to grab the key but if you can Jess will be friends with Leo again. Do your best to return to Jess with {C=0xFFFF5917/}Captain Hookah's Secret Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Conversation with Jess at Bearded Whale Coast

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Leo is worried because Jess is very angry for some reason. He doesn't know why but whenever Jess has been angry before it's because he was in some kind of trouble. Go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and speak to {C=0xFF00863C/}Jess{C=0xFF4D0D08/} before he does anything foolish.%%

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 30 Jellies and Red Jellies at the Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Bearded Whale Coast used to be very famous for the number of Bearded Whales you could see there. Since the Jelly and Red Jelly population exploded the number of Bearded Whales in the area have been in decline, a research group have identified the Jellies Slime is very acidic and a threat to the environment.
To protect the Bearded Whales go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 15 Whale Tears from Shark Pirates at the Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mukapa has found another reason for the decline in the number of Whales around the coast. The Shark Pirates have been catching the whales to extract their Tears. Each whales magical energy comes from their tears and without them they get weak and eventually die. To save the whales who have already lost their tears go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get back {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Whale Tears{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Captain Hookah at the Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mukapa has found out why the Shark Pirates have been extracting the Whale Tears. They have been trading them on the black market at very high prices, the demand for them is very high due to their great beauty.
Captain Hookah is the main one behind all of this, to protect the Bearded Whales defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Captain Hookah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Wooden Boxes from Crabbies at the Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jess has lost the Wooden Boxes he has keeping his collection in. He had hidden them all around the Bearded Whale Coast, Jess suspects that Captain Hookah must have learnt about this and took them in revenge for when Jess took his boxes.
Jess thinks the Crabby are looking after his boxes for Hookah. Bring Jess {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Wooden Boxes{C=0xFF4D0D08/} obtained from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Treasure Chests from Shark Pirates at the Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos mode(F2)].

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jess suddenly started screaming out! He realised that all of his Treasure Chests had gone, he stored everything he collected in them.
Jess is angry at Captain Hookah and his henchmen, he believes it was the Shark Pirates who took the Treasure Chests from him in revenge. Calm down Jess by collecting {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Treasure Chests{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and returning them.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring back Jess's Treasure Chest Key from Captain Hookah at the Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jess is in a panic after realising he has lost the key to his chest. He has tried to remember where he lost it and remembered when he was trying t approach Captain Hookah a few days ago to see if he had anything worth stealing. He was caught by his henchman and just about managed to run away, when he turned back he saw Captain Hookah picking up something shiny. It must have been the key.
If you want to stop hearing Jess's crying and mourning bring back his {C=0xFFFF5917/}Treasure Chest Key{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Captain Hookah{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Starry Lala at Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Primo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Primo was minding his own business fishing when he felt something hit him. It was the Starry Lala's, they were teasing him for the size of his waist and kept hitting his hips and teasing him.
Primo told them to stop but they hit him again and ran away.
Go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Starry Lala{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Shark Pirates and Starry Lulu at the Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Primo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Primo really enjoys late night fishing. A couple days ago he was enjoying some night fishing when Shark Pirates and Starry Lulus came out of nowhere and surprised him!
They thought Primo looked like a legendary sea monster and were very disappoint when they realised that wasn't the case. They said if Primo ever goes night fishing again they will make him pay for it.
For poor Primo make the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/} pay for their bullying. There are at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring back 20 Earthworms from Starry Lolo and Razor Crabbies at the Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bearded Whale Coast - Primo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Someone took the Earthworms that Primo was planning to use for fishing bait. Without bait Primo says he cannot even catch a blind fish.
Primo thinks it was the Starry Lolo and Razor Crabby at the Bearded Whale Coast. He saw them hurrying away from where he was storing his Earthworms.
Bring back Primo's {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Earthworms{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lolos{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Razor Crabby{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Bearded Whale Coast [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring 20 Crabby Roe from Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Daisy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Daisy is very excited because she has found a forbidden potion recipe. The recipe lists the ingredients required to create a love potion created by a wizard a long time ago. The wizard quickly realised how dangerous the recipe was if it fell into the wrong hands and sealed it away, but Daisy has managed to get the recipe. She wants your help to gather the required ingredients, bring her {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Crabby Roe{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get 20 Starry Stock from Starry Lulus and Starry Lolos at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Daisy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Daisy is not happy because the love potion requires too many ingredients. One of the ingredients she needs is Starry Stock, it can be obtained from Starry Lulus and Starry Lolos.
Daisy says that because they are so skinny it can be hard to get the stock from them. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and bring back {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Starry Stock{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lulus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lolos{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 15 Magic Black Pearls from Shark Pirate at Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Wind - Daisy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Daisy is very excited because there is only one ingredient left to gather for the love potion. It's called a Magical Black Pearl, they are created sometimes when a Shark Pirates wound is healed. Getting Magical Black Pearls from violent Shark Pirates will not be easy, but Daisy has faith in your ability.
Bring back {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Magic Black Pearls{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 30 Shark Pirates at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Davy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Rumours have been spreading among the Shark community that Davy is giving out free stuff. Different sharks from different areas all over Dragotaka have been coming to Davy recently demanding free stuff, recently it has been Shark Pirates from Steven Trading Port.
Head over to {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to help kill the rumours.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Meteorite Fragments from Shark Deckhands at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Davy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
While you were taking care of the Shark Pirates at Steven Trading Port for Davy some Shark Deckhands must have slipped past you and started demanding more free stuff from Davy.
Davy refused their demands so instead they stole Davy's Meteorite Fragments from his display. Davy was keeping the fragments to make some awesome equipment with, they are very valuable to him.
Bring back Davy's {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Meteorite Fragments{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 40 Shark Pirates and Shark Deckhands at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Davy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Davy says the Shark Pirates and Shark Deckhands keep coming and making threats at Davy because they heard the rumour he was giving away free stuff!
Because Davy won't give them the stuff they demand they have threatened to destroy his smithery.
Slay 40 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/} or {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to protect Davy.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 20 Starry Lulu and 20 Starry Lolo at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mukapa wants to know how the humans face danger. Mukapa warns that danger lurks and can strike at anytime on any day. He says its best to make pre-emptive strikes against threats before they become a danger.
Mukapa already views the number of Starry Lulu and Starry Lolo at Steven Trading Port a potential threat, slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Starry Lolo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Achieve a 300 Combo at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
You have learned how to prevent danger, but for the times when you cannot see danger approaching you must lean how to act fast.
It takes lots of training to learn how to do this, Drakans use Combos to learn how to be fast. Learn how to be quick when facing danger by achieving a {C=0xFFFF5917/}300 Combo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Razor Crabby at Kalygon Fleet

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mukapa is still teaching you how to face danger. Another important factor to consider when facing new dangers is strength. There are times when being fast cannot save you, this is when strength will help you to overcome such dangers. To learn how to have strength taking on a monster with a strong shell, like Razor Crabby at Kalygon Fleet would be perfect for your training.
Slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Razor Crabby{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 40 Starry Lulu, Starry Lala, Starry Lolo at Kalygon Fleet

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Mukapa

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mukapa says that the Drakan have higher mental abilities than the humans. Such mental abilities can only be obtained through lots of conditioning. There are some humans who have achieved these higher mental abilities through very long and hard training.
The strongest factor when facing danger is to have a fighting spirit, meaning you should never give up. Learn how the meaning of having a fighting spirit by slaying {C=0xFFFF5917/}40 Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lala{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lolo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Punk Hippos, Biker Hippos and Charming Hippos at Temple of Water

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Anna

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Anna went to the Temple of Water recently because she heard of the excellent fishing in there. She took everything she needed to catch the best fish but as she was busy being amazed by the beautiful fish the Hippos ate all of her bait! Go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Temple of Water{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Punk Hippos{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Biker Hippos{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Charming Hippos{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 20 Puffer Roes from Young Swellfish, Breeding Swellfish and Single Swellfish at the Temple of Water

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Hena

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Anna has heard about a dangerous Roe dish, Anna thinks this is so dangerous it has to be investigated. She says the Puffer Roes are kept by {C=0xFFFF5917/}Breeding Swellfish{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and the Puffer Roes are protected by {C=0xFFFF5917/}Young Swellfish{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Single Swellfish{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. This task is too dangerous for someone like Anna, help her with her investigation by returning with {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Puffer Roe{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 20 Abandoned Quartz Golem and Broken Jewel Golem at the Temple of Water

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Hena

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Anna says there is a legendary fishing bait hidden within the Temple of Water. It's too dangerous for any normal fisherman to go in there and attempt to obtain the bait. Anna would like to know if you are strong enough to reach the legendary bait deep within the temple and get it back to her. Show Anna how strong you are by slaying {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Abandoned Quartz Golem{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Broken Jewel Golem{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}Temple of Water{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Golem Cores from Mossy Golems in the Temple of Water

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Anna

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Anna tells you about one of the legendary baits she knows of, the Golem Core.
Golem cores can only be obtained from Mossy Golems in the Temple of Water. The story comes from a warrior who entered the temple a long time ago, one of the Mossy Golems he had slain fell into a large fishing pool. Shortly after the warrior saw hundreds of fish gathering around the Golems Core....
Bring back {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Golem Cores{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mossy Golems{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}Temple of Water{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 20 Rakerta's Tails from Seafood Seller Dile and Luxurious Dile at the Temple of Water

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Anna

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Anna says she has found a bait that will enable her to catch a Sea lion! Sea lions are known for being the best hunters at sea and even professional fisherman cannot catch them. Sea lions only like really large bait, but they also have a soft spot for Rakerta's Tails.
Rakertas are extinct now but apparently {C=0xFFFF5917/}Seafood Seller Dile{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Luxurious Dile{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the {C=0xFF016295/}Temple of Water{C=0xFF4D0D08/} have them. Bring back {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Rakerta's Tails{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Anna.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring back the 10 pages of the Book of Sages that Shark Pirates and  Shark Deckhands stole.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Jeremy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
As Jeremy was walking home through Steven Trading Port with his Book of Sages he was mugged by a group of Shark Pirates and Shark Deckhands. Jeremy's book contains lots of knowledge about the world of Dragotaka and if it falls into the wrong hands it could be used for all manner of evils. Before the Sharks work out the importance of the book go to {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and claim back {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Book of Sages Pages{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 40 Jellies and Red Jellies at Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Jeremy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jeremy is glad to have his Book of Sages back, but when he opened it he found it was covered in the Jellies Slime! The acidic slime will cause the book to disintegrate... Only the Jellies and Red Jellies at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} are known for damaging books like this.
Head over there and slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}40 Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to ensure the safety of the worlds books.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring back 10 Purifying Cleansers from Starry Lala at Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Jeremy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jeremy says he has found a way to save his Book of Sages from the acidic slime. Some Purifying Cleanser would not only neutralise the slime and stop the book from disintegrating but it will also make the book look almost as good as new.
Jeremy will need {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Purifying Cleansers{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, they can only be found on {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lalas{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Starry Lulus at Kalygon Fleet

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Leo wanted to test his new sword skills so went to Kalygon Fleet to battle with a Starry Lulu. He was doing well in the battle but half way through the Starry Lulu called his friends and Leo was surrounded by over thirty of them! Leo managed to run away but he cannot forgive the Starry Lulu for his dirty tactics.
Leo want's you to ensure the Starry Lulu cannot call for backup during his next fight. Slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet{C=0xFF4D0D08/} so Leo may finish the battle without being outnumbered.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring back Leo's Necklace from Starry Lulu at Kalygon Fleet [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Leo went back to the Starry Lulu for another battle. The Starry Lulu was trying even harder than last time so it was a difficult battle but Leo managed to come out on top in the end. Leo dropped his necklace during the battle without realising, the Lulu grabbed the necklace and ran away to {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} . The necklace was given to him by his mother who has now passed away and holds great sentimental value. Leo is asking you for help to get the necklace back...
Go and get {C=0xFFFF5917/}Leo's Necklace{C=0xFF4D0D08/} back from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 15 Crabby Sticks from Crabbies at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Crispin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Crispin uses a special polish to keep his products shiny, the problem is he has run out and his import order of polish never arrived, probably due to the pirates creating a blockade. As a result Crispin has been experimenting with other things to see if they can be used as polish and discovered that Crabby Sticks are a perfect replacement. The problem is they're very violent making them hard to get. Help Crispin by collecting {C=0xFFFF5917/} 15 Crabby Sticks{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and brining them back to him.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 15 Starry Lolo and 15 Starry Lulu at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Crispin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Crispin has been looking for a way to get home for weeks, but there have been no ships coming or leaving because of the pirates blockade. Luckily Steven Jr is issuing a special boarding pass so people can go home using the Military Ship.
Crispin collected the boarding pass for himself and his friends but has lost it after being attacked at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Clear {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Starry Lolo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}15 Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the area so Crispin can go and search for it.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Pouches that the Shark Pirates and Shark Deckhands picked up at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Crispin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Crispin went to look for his Pouch which contained the Boarding Pass he had collected for his friends. The area was already swarmed in Shark Pirates and Shark Deckhands, Crispin asked them for his Pouch back but they just laughed at him.
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and bring back {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Crispin's Pouches{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak with Croquis at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Trading Port - Croquis

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Crispin has been searching for information about his lost Boarding Pass and mentioned that {C=0xFF00863C/}Croquis{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, a Drakan, has been training around {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Since he has been training around the port perhaps he knows something about the boarding passes. Go and speak to him while Crispin looks for the passes elsewhere.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hunt 30 Jelly and Red Jelly at the Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Trading Port - Croquis

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Croquis cannot trust you enough to share the whereabouts of the boarding pass and would like to test you to allow you to earn some trust. 
Show how important the Boarding Pass is to you and gain his trust by hunting {C=0xFFFF5917/}30 Jelly{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Jelly{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
Red Jelly are in several different maps, so you might need to try more than one.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Boarding Passes from sharks at Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode(F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Trading Port - Croquis

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Croquis saw some Sharks while on a walk around Steven Trading Port with something which matched the description of the Boarding Pass. He says he isn't entirely sure it was the Pass they were carrying, but they were carrying some paper and looked incredibly happy with themselves. He saw there were exactly 10 pieces of paper.
The {C=0xFFFF5917/}Sharks{C=0xFF4D0D08/} were heading to {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode (F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, collect {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Boarding Passes{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from them.
 Sharks hide in several different maps, so you may need to try more than one.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Genuine Boarding Passes from Shark Deckhand at Steven Trading Port [Chaos Mode(F2)] and take them to Crispin at Port of the Winds

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Crispin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Croquis believes the Sharks changed the Genuine Boarding Pass with the Shark Deckhands Inn entrance ticket. The Military ship is a very safe method of travel and has no security checks to get on-board, so many people are buying boarding passes for a high price. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Genuine Boarding Passes{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take them safely to Crispin at Port of the Winds.
The Shark Deckhands hide in different maps so you might need to try more than one.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Conversation with Sijin at Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Trading Port - Sijin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Victor at Port of the Winds is good friends with Sijin at Steven Trading Port. They are both artists and enjoy meeting up and critiquing each others work. They leave their work with each other for a while so they can formulate their opinions on each piece and meet later to discuss it with each other. Sijin is very forgetful and Victor want's you to remind him of the meeting they are meant to have soon.
Make sure {C=0xFF00863C/}Sijin{C=0xFF4D0D08/} hasn't forgotten about it, you can find him at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Bring back Sijin's stuff back from Jelly and Red jelly at Decker Shark Piers

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Trading Port - Sijin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sijin was on patrol a the Decker Shark Piers a while ago, and had a feeling he had left something there. After you came to him he realised that it was probably Victor's sculpture. The {C=0xFFFF5917/}Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in that area like to go around collecting random things. They probably picked up the sculpture, get it back from one of the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} or {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Decker Shark Piers{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Get back the Round Eyed Sculpture from Sharks at Decker Shark Pier

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Victor

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sijin says he saw a Shark carrying Victor's Round Eyed Sculpture.
The Sharks are very violent and probably won't take care of the sculpture and Sijin cannot risk it being damaged or Victor will never forgive him. Sijin cannot leave his post, get back Victors {C=0xFFFF5917/}Round Eyed Sculpture{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Sharks{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Decker Shark Piers{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Sijin thinks it would be safest if you take it directly back to Victor.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 10 Starry Lulu, 10 Starry Lolo, and 10 Starry Lala at Kalygon Fleet

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Jeremy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jeremy says he's worried about Leo to go dangerous place, {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, over and over again. He says it's very dangerous since there are  many {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Lolo{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Lala{C=0xFF4D0D08/} attacking children. To stop those monsters attacking children, defeat 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Lolo{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Lala{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for each from {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Take Leo's Father's Dagger from Razor Crabby in Kalygon Fleet

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jeremy thinks he has found out why Leo keeps putting himself into danger by going to Kalygon Fleet. He has heard from the residents of Port of the Winds that a Razor Crabby there has been carrying a dagger which looks just like the one that belonged to Leo's Father. Leo missing his parents very much and it's likely that he has been going to the fleet in search of this dagger.
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take {C=0xFFFF5917/}Leo's Father's Dagger{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Razor Crabby{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. When you have found it, give it to Leo.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect 10 Letters from Leo's parents from Jellies at Kalygon Fleet [Arcade Mode (F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Leo says he doesn't have a very clear memory about the accident, but being given his father's dagger has helped him remember a few details. He remembers his parents put him on a lifeboat, but there was not enough room for them all and they remained on the doomed ship. His parent's hugged him and told him they would write a letter and leave it in a bottle so if they didn't make it to safety someday Leo could find the letter. Leo recalls many {C=0xFFFF5917/}Jellies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} coming aboard the boat as it was sinking, they have a habit of collecting papers. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet [Arcade Mode (F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Letters from Leo's Parents{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
They like to travel to different places often so you should select at least two maps. You may need to try more than once.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Collect the Captain's Log from Kalygon at Kalygon Fleet [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Leo is disappointed to find that there were no details about the incident written in the letter from his parents. Leo assumes his parents didn't want to him to know the truth surrounding the tragedy.
Leo is aware that ship captains keep logs of everything that happens on their voyage. Leo hopes that the Captain's Log from that day may hold some vital information on what happened on that tragic day.
The log probably washed up at Kalygon Fleet and Kalygon keeps everything found around there.
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Captain's Log{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Kalygon{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 20 Mad Kalygons and Shark Deckhands at Kalygon Fleet [Chaos Mode(F2)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
According to the Captain's log, the ship struck a rock when it was travelling past Kalygon Fleet and trying to evade Kalygon's Shark Deckhands. The lifeboat was overturned in the rough seas while trying to run from them. Fight for justice by defeating {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Mad Kalygons{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak to Sijin in Steven Trading Port

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Trading Port - Sijin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Victor has heard from Guard Sijin that there's some suspicious activity in Steven Trading Port. He requested that Victor report this immediately to his superiors to ask for support troops to help him. Currently the defence forces of Port of the Winds are spread thin and Victor's superiors want concrete evidence before they sent any already overstretched resources.
Help {C=0xFF00863C/}Sijin{C=0xFF4D0D08/} gather enough evidence, speak to him at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port {C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 20 Starry Lulu at Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Trading Port - Sijin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sijin has heard a rumour that pirates from Steven Trading Port and Kalygon fleet have created an alliance and are conspiring together to create a plan to attack Port of the Winds. He's not entirely certain as the Lulu as very merry, probably on his way home from the Inn, when he heard him murmuring about it. To help slow down these plans head to {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Starry Lulu{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
The Lulus are often on the move so you should check more than two maps at once, you might need to try more than once.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Gather 5 Attack Plans from Shark Pirate at Steven Trading Port [Chaos Mode(F2)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Trading Port - Sijin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sijin thinks he has another clue regarding the planned attack on Port of the Winds. The Attack Plans should have all of the planned strategies the pirates plan to use to attack Port of the Winds. Apparently the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Pirates{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Steven Trading Port [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} are currently in possession of the plans.
Because the Sharks Pirates are currently in the middle of planning an attack be very careful, they will surely be very violent and will show you no mercy since you're putting their plans in jeopardy.
Collet {C=0xFFFF5917/}5 Attack Plans{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from them.
They move around a lot to protect their location so select at least two maps, you may need to try a few times.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 20 Crabby at Kalygon Fleet [Arcade Mode(F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Trading Port - Sijin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sijin has found out that it's the Crabbies from Kalygon Fleet [Arcade Mode(F1)] who are planning to attack Port of the Winds alongside the Starry Lulu according to the Attack Plans.
They seem to have some kind of alliance with each other. Put a halt to their attack plans, slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}20 Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet [Arcade Mode (F1)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
The Crabbies move around a lot to prevent themselves from being found. Select at least two maps, you may need to try a few times.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 20 Shark Deckhands at Kalygon Fleet [Chaos mode(F2)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Steven Trading Port - Sijin

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sijin has finally formulated a clear picture of who is leading at attack on Port of the Winds. Just like before, the Starry Lala visited him again on his way home from the Inn. The Lala said there's a new Inn in Port of the Winds and it has really delicious drinks. The {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shark Deckhands{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet [Chaos Mode(F2)]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} are known for enjoying a good drink and must be the masterminds behind this plan, they are the ones that have created the alliance with the Starry Lulu from Steven Trading Port and Crabbies from Kalygon Fleet to rob the Inn in Port of the Winds together.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver Sijin's Friendly Letter to Hime at Moonlight Shore Village

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sijin hasn't had a chance to visit his cousin in Moonlight Shore village for over a year. Sijin would like it if you would deliver his {C=0xFFFF5917/}Friendly Letter{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to his cousin {C=0xFF00863C/}Hime{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF00863C/}Moonlight Shore Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} so they can keep in touch.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 25 Spiked Mace Mummies in Skippy Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hime loves to go on adventures around the sanctuaries in the hope of unlocking some of their secrets. He was wandering around Skippy Sanctuary and bumped into a Spiked Mace Mummy earlier. The mummy swung his mace at him and Hime had to dive to the ground to avoid it, ruining his new clothes.
Hime is furious about it and wants you to slay 25 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spiked Mace Mummy{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to teach it a lesson.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Slay 25 Skull Thunkers in Skippy Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Something hard hit Hime on the head while he was gathering herbs in Skippy Sanctuary. When he jumped back to his feet he realised there were a few Skull Thunkers throwing things at him. Hime left the sanctuary immediately but he still has a big lump on his head.
Slay {C=0xFFFF5917/}25 Skull Thunkers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to teach them a lesson at {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 10 Aloe Vera Plants from Blue Spectral Knights, Spectral Blood Knights and Spectral Dragon Knights in Skippy Sanctuary.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hime is suffering from really itchy skin. He needs some Aloe Vera Plants to help relive it, the plant is sometimes found in Skippy Sanctuary and when mashed up helps relive itchy skin.
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect {C=0xFFFF5917/}10 Aloe Vera Plants{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Blue Spectral Knights{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spectral Blood Knights{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spectral Dragon Knights{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 15 Skin Cleansers from Spiked Mace Mummy in Skippy Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hime says his itchy skin won't be relived that easily. The Aloe Vera Plant helped to ease the pain, but it's not a permanent solution. To cure the problem he needs some Skin Cleanser. It contains some active ingredients which help cure all kinds of skin problems. The {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spiked Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} are big uses of the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skin Cleanser{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. It's what stops them decomposing. Obtain 15 of them for Hime.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 15 Tattered Bandages from Mummies in the Underground Graveyard

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Swirl

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Swirl really needs some better bandages to treat the Moonlight Shore Villagers. The bandages he collected himself from Mirinae Sanctuary were no good at all.
Go to the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Underground Graveyard{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to get 15 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Tattered Bandages{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Swirl. They're bound to have some great healing properties.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Jess, Hunter G, and Larell in Moonlight Shore Village

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Swirl

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Claire entrusted her ring to Swirl for a little while, however the ring seems to have been stolen from Swirl's house while he was out for a short period of time. Swirl has three suspects in mind, they're {C=0xFF00863C/}Jess{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFF00863C/}Hunter G{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and {C=0xFF00863C/}Larell{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
Speak to the three suspects and return to Swirl with any clues you find.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 15 Strong tooth from Slithers in Underground Graveyard.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Smith

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Smith is trying to create a new weapon he's designed.
The weapon is a Strong Tooth which can chew on anything using a strong jaw. He would like your assistance in collecting the materials he needs to create the Strong Tooth.
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Underground Graveyard{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Slithers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to collect 15 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Strong Teeth{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take them to {C=0xFF00863C/}Smith{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Katler in the Underground Graveyard

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jess thinks he's found some information about the criminal who stole Claire's ring from Swirl.
Before he tells you about this clue he would like you to complete a favour for him.
Go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Underground Graveyard{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Katler{C=0xFF4D0D08/} before returning to Jess for the information.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Graveyard Mummies in the Underground Graveyard

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Larell

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Larell has had a headache for a long time. He finds that it is because Underground Graveyard Mummies make noise. Go to Underground Graveyard and defeat Underground Graveyard Mummy for Larell.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 200 monsters in the Underground Graveyard

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Frank

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Equipment Merchant Frank is seeking some unique items to attract some special customers. Frank believes there are precious items down in the Underground Graveyard, go down there for him and defeat 200 monsters and return to Frank with your findings.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Bone Frag in the Underground Graveyard

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Frank

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Equipment Merchant Frank thinks people are much less motivated for adventure and willing to accept challenges, people are falling into depression.
He says this is the time for a hero to appear and encourage young people to overcome their hardships.
Go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Underground Graveyard{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Bone Frag{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to help Frank show people how to overcome their depression.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
 Obtain 20 Claire's cheese from Master Sprinters in Underground Graveyard

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Claire

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Innkeeper Claire says she prepared some cheese for her children about a year ago, but when she was carrying them to her warehouse some Master Sprinters turned up and stole all of the cheese! Go to the {C=0xFF016295/}Underground Graveyard{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Master Sprinters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to find {C=0xFFFF5917/}Claire's Cheese{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Collect 20 and take them to Claire.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 15 Rusty Swords from Headless Fencers in the Underground Graveyard

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Claire

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thomas, the head of the mercenary clan wants to begin preparations to make his clan powerful and legendary as they were once in the past. He would like you to collect 15 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Rusty Swords{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Headless Fencers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in the {C=0xFF016295/}Underground Graveyard{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take them to Claire who is expecting them.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
 Defeat Ratler in the Underground Graveyard

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - James

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
A few days ago James's kitty MingMing was acting strangely after he had been to the Underground Graveyard. He returned scared stiff! He seems to have been frightened by Ratle. Go down into the {C=0xFF016295/}Underground Graveyard{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Ratler{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in revenge for MingMing!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1] - Retrieve 15 Smooth 'Brick Red' Fabric from Mummy Boxers

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Sofia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sofia has started a second job, she has started making clothes after her bank work is completed each day. Even though she's only just started she has already received an order! Cindy from Port of the Winds wants something that suit's her personality.
Help Sofia out by going to {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and retrieve 15 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Smooth 'Brick Red' Fabric{C=0xFF4D0D08/} pieces from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mummy Boxers{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Retrieve 10 Delicate Beads from Mummy Fighters in Skippy Sanctuary[Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Cindy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sofia has completed crafting the clothes for the order from Sofia in Port of the Winds. However, it's not as good as she originally thought. She thinks some additional decoration would make it much better! Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Delicate Beads{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mummy Fighters{C=0xFF4D0D08/} before taking the garment to Cindy.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 5 of the First Jewels from Skull Clubber in Skippy Sanctuary[Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Jess heard some interesting story. According to the rumour, a brave warrior passed away protecting the village. The warrior has been buried with two Jewels beneath the Sanctuary. Go to Skippy Sanctuary[Arcade Mode F1], defeat Skull Clubber and retrieve first Jewel.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
 Obtain the Second Jewel from the Lord of Night in Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Jess

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sneaky Thief Jess says he was disappointed after he saw the first jewel you brought back, however Jess has found some more information about the Second Jewel.
Follow Jess's instructions and go to {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Lord of Night{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to find the Second Jewel before returning to Jess.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Skull Runners in Skippy Sanctuary[Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Larell

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Graveyard Keeper Larell has been suffering from Nightmares for days! He's sure they are caused by the wicked noises coming from Skippy Sanctuary, they're really stressing him out.
Help Larell out by slaying 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skull Runners{C=0xFF4D0D08/} who are making the wicked sounds in {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Skull Thunkers in Skippy Sanctuary[Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Larell

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Graveyard Keeper Larell has been unable to sleep recently. The nasty Skull Thunkers have been throwing rocks at him whenever he has tried to take a nap. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Larell and defeat 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skull Thunkers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} so he can rest in peace.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 15 Skull Clubbers in Skippy Sanctuary[Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Larell

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The Skull Clubbers have been coming to Larell's Graveyard and damaging the Gravestones. Larell want's you to teach the Skull Clubbers some respect. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat 15 of the immature {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skull Clubbers{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Report to Larell once you're done.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade (F1)] - Defeat 10 Blue Spectral Knight

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Jesse

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Frank keeps teasing Jesse that he's an old scrooge who only cares about money. Jesse got really angry and said he would show Frank how strong he really is. To cover Jesse's exaggerated story let's go to Skippy Sanctuary[Arcade Mode(F1)], and defeat 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Blue Spectral Knight{C=0xFF4D0D08/} as Jasse requested.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 20 Rusty helmets from Blue Spectral Knight in Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thomas seeks to restore the past glory of his mercenary group. It doesn't have many members at the moment but just in-case there's a surge in new members, Thomas is collecting equipment. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Rusty Helmets{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Blue Spectral Knights{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Talk to Claire

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Claire

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Larell cannot remember much from his childhood and is curious about where he was born and raised. He recently received an anonymous letter from someone containing a photo of when he was young. Larell says the background of the photo seems to be the inn in {C=0xFF016295/}Moonlight Shore Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Go and speak to {C=0xFF00863C/}Claire{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at the inn and see if she knows anything about Larell's childhood.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 10 Mallet Mummies, 10 Mace Mummies and 10 Spiked Mace Mummies in Parmir Sanctuary.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - James

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
James is planning on building a Winery Village over Parmir Sanctuary. James hopes it will create lots of revenue once it starts operating. There is just one problem James's business partner, Rudolph, needs to overcome. There are loads of monsters wandering around the Sanctuary. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Parmir Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mallet Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spiked Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and then return to James.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Talk to Rudolph

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Rudolph

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Larell is concerned that building the Winery Village over Parmir Sanctuary will be disastrous to Dragotaka's Cultural Heritage. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and tell {C=0xFF00863C/}Rudolph{C=0xFF4D0D08/} about Larell's concerns.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Retrieve 20 Cute Fossils from Spectral Dragon Knights in Parmir Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Claire

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Amy has been collecting Cute Fossils for Innkeeper Claire so she may decorate her inn. Amy found many fossils for her, but on her way back from Parmir Sanctuary she was attacked by Spectral Dragon Knights and they stole all of the fossils!
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Parmir Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and retrieve 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Cute Fossils{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Once you have them take them straight to Claire.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mirinae Sanctuary - Retrieve 20 Shark's Fin from Mummy Boxer

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Claire

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Inn keeper Claire is planning to enter Best Ramen Chef Competition. With the winning prize, she is planning to feed the children. Claire is planning to Make a Special Ramen with a Shark's Fin, a Shark's Fin Ramen if you will. However, Mummy Boxer's have stolen all of her Shark's Fin's. Go to Mirinae Sanctuary and retrieve 20 Shark's Fin from Mummy Boxer.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mirinae Sanctuary - Retrieve 20 sack of grain from Blue Spectral Knight

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Sofia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banker Sofia is planning to enter the Best Ramen Chef competition, and she is studying the Ramen after her work is finished. Sofia purchased a Special Flour to make a best tasting noodle, but it was stolen by Blue Spectral Knight at Mirinae Sanctuary. Go to Mirinae Sanctuary and retrieve 20 sack of grain from Blue Spectral Knight.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 20 Mummy Jerky pieces from Crimson Mace Mummies in Mirinae Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mercenary Thomas is entering the Best Ramen Chef Competition. He believes the Ramen he used to eat when he was young is good enough to win! A special recipe from his mother, the Ramen has a very strong flavour that's unforgettable. Help Thomas by obtaining 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mummy Jerky{C=0xFF4D0D08/} pieces from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Crimson Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, the special ingredient.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 15 Sparks at Dangerous Caverns

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Smith

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Blacksmith Smith has ordered lots of new hammers. But Sparks have robbed the hammers while they were being delivered. Smith is desperate for new hammers as he only has one left and has many repairs to complete.
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Dangerous Caverns{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Sparks{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Smith.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 10 Mage Dudus in Dangerous Caverns

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Smith

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Blacksmith Smith is always receiving requests from villagers.
He has a kind heart and never refuses any requests, Smith would like your help to complete a request that he cannot complete alone. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Dangerous Caverns{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mage Dudus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Smith, and to keep the villagers happy.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 10 Torn up Receipt Pieces in Mirinae Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1] 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Smith

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Blacksmith Smith says he say Frank tearing up some receipts so he could avoid paying some of his taxes. At first he thought he could just turn a blind eye, but his conscience just won't let him.
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Mirinae Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skull Runners{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and search them to find 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Torn up Receipt Pieces{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. When you're done, take them to Smith.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Smith in Moonlight Shore Village

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Smith

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Equipment Merchant Frank was caught by the police for throwing away some receipts so he could avoid paying some of his taxes. Because Smith saw him and reported it to the police, Frank had to pay a fine.
Frank says he was in bad shape because of the economy and made a mistake, but says he is disappointed that Smith reported him. Let's help Frank and Smith understand each other.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Innkeeper Florence in Odelia

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Odelia - Florence

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Innkeeper Claire borrowed some land from James a few days ago. She's decided to plant some Cheese Apple trees there. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Odelia{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and ask {C=0xFF00863C/}Florence{C=0xFF4D0D08/} about how these trees can be grown for her.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Find 20 Apple seeds from Spiked Mace Mummy in Skippy Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Claire

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Florence in Odelia has completed collecting information about the Cheese Apple for Claire, but these days no one ever plants this type of tree, but the seed may still be able to be found.
Based on Florence's Research, she thinks it should be possible to find 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Apple Seeds{C=0xFF4D0D08/} on {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spiked Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Claire.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Skull Thunker in Skippy Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Claire

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Innkeeper Claire is planning to plant the Cheese Apple seeds in the area that James gave to her. There is just one obstacle standing in her way. There are many dangerous Skull Thunkers wandering around.
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Skippy Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat 30 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skull Thunkers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to clear the way and allow Claire to begin planting the apple trees!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Victor in Port of Winds

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Victor

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Guard Swirl and Victor from Port of the Winds have been very close friends ever since they were young.
Unfortunately they are now assigned as Guards in different towns and haven't spoken in a long time. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and give {C=0xFF00863C/}Victor{C=0xFF4D0D08/} Swirls best regards!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 10 Pincers from Razor Crabby at Kalygon Fleet

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Swirl

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Victor at Port of the Winds and Swirl at Moonlight Shore Village are very good friends. Victor would like to get some Pincers for Swirl, it's one of Swirl's favourite foods. Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Kalygon Fleet{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect 10 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Pincers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} by defeating {C=0xFFFF5917/}Razor Crabbies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and take them to Swirl.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver Crabby Claws Lunch Set to Victor in Port of Winds - 

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Victor

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Swirl in Moonlight Shore Village made a delicious Pincers dish. He hopes his friend Victor can have a taste of how delicious it is.
Deliver the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Crabby Claws Lunch Set{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to {C=0xFF00863C/}Victor{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Spectral Dragon Knights in Parmir Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hime in Moonlight Shore Village has been very concerned that his best selling potion won't be available for sale for much longer. It's made from some special herbs he grows himself in a herb grove, but some Spectral Dragon Knights keep invading the grove and destroying the herbs.
Defeat 30 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spectral Dragon Knights{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to protect Hime's Herb Grove and ensure he can continue selling his best potion.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Mace Mummy and 20 Spiked Mace Mummy at Parmir Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thomas is trying hard to re-establish his Mercenary Army. Thomas sent the weapons you collected to Libra to be repaired and was expecting them back a while ago. The delivery has not been able to pass through {C=0xFF016295/}Parmir Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} because {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spiked Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} are blocking the way!
Defeat 20 of each of them so the delivery can get through to Thomas!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 20 Focusing Lenses from Mace Mummy and Spiked Mace Mummy at Parmir Sanctuary.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tool Merchant Hime created 20 Focusing Lenses for Rudolph's Solar Powered Machine. On his way to deliver them {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Spiked Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Parmir Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} stole them!
Get them back for Hime!

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Rudolph in Port of the Winds

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Rudolph

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hime has recruited some mercenaries from Thomas to guard him while he delivers the Focusing Lens to Rudolph. He's just waiting for them to turn up, let {C=0xFF00863C/}Rudolph{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/} that his package may be slightly delayed.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Warn Thomas in Moonlight Shore Village

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Little Thief Jess saw a number of monsters acting strangely near the Moonlight Shore.
Jess believes they may be preparing to attack the village soon, but this information must be delivered by someone trustworthy.
Jess would like you to go to Mercenary Leader {C=0xFF00863C/}Thomas{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and deliver the message.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 30 Lunch Bags from Blue Spectral Knight in Mirinae Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thomas is acting on the news that monsters may be preparing to attack the village. Blue Spectral Knights have taken over the wagon that was carrying food to the village, they have taken all of the Soldiers Lunch Bags. They won't be happy when they hear!
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Mirinae Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and get back 30 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Lunch Bags{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Blue Spectral Knights{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and give them to Thomas.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Skull Clubbers and 20 Skull Thunkers in Mirinae Sanctuary.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thomas is taking the news that monsters are about to invade the village very seriously. He plans to make a pre-emptive strike on them before they get a chance to move forward with their plan. To protect the village, follow Thomas's orders and defeat 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skull Clubbers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skull Thunkers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Mirinae Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 20 Crimson Mace Mummies and 20 Mummy Boxers

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
After a successful attack, Thomas is ready to start a second strike.
Thomas would like to you go to {C=0xFF016295/}Mirinae Sanctuary [Arcade Mode F1]{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Crimson Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mummy Boxers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to ensure they can't hit us first.
When complete report back to Thomas.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Battle Plan from Artis in Mirinae Sanctuary [Arcade (F1)]

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Thomas has defeated many monsters in the area surrounding Moonlight Shore Village thanks to his very wise strategy.
Thomas has one last stage to his plan to save the village from attack. Defeat the leader of the monsters, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Artis{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and take his {C=0xFFFF5917/}Battle Plan{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to put a complete stop to all of the attacks from the monsters.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Deliver a letter to Frank in Moonlight Shore Village

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Frank

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tool Merchant Hime is competing against Frank in Moonlight Shore Village to make the most sales.
Hime wasn't happy with the taunts Frank made about Hime's low sales and wants you to deliver a Challenge to him!
{C=0xFF00863C/}Frank{C=0xFF4D0D08/} can be found in {C=0xFF016295/}Moonlight Shore Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Talk to Hime in Moonlight Shore Village

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The challenge from Hime has been accepted by Frank and things are beginning to heat up! Frank wants you to tell Hime that they will compare their profits in a weeks time to determine who is the winner.
Go and tell {C=0xFF00863C/}Hime{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Moonlight Shore Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/} the rules of the challenge.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 30 Mummy Boxers in Belkan Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Hime and Franks challenge has already been going for a couple of days. Hime has ordered a special potion to ensure he can beat Frank, but the delivery is being delayed by some Mummy Boxers.
Go to {C=0xFF016295/}Belkan Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and defeat 30 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mummy Boxers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} to ensure the delivery can arrive safely.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 30 Red herbs from Red Spectral Knights in Belkan Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
The competition between Frank and Hime is still on-going. Hime really thinks he can beat Frank this time, but one of his new top selling potions has a bad smell.
Hime thinks he can sell more of this potion but needs to do something about the smell. Red Herbs are really good at making potions smell better, but Red Spectral Knights stole them!
Defeat {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Spectral Knights{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Belkan Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and collect 30 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Red Herbs{C=0xFF4D0D08/} for Hime.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Crimson Mace Mummies and retrieve 20 Green Herbs at Belkan Sanctuary

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Frank and Hime are having a competition to see who can get the most profit in a week. Hime thinks he is really close to beating Frank for once.
Hime needs some Green Herbs to improve his potion after the Red Herbs made it smell better, but reduced it's effectiveness.
{C=0xFFFF5917/}Green Herbs{C=0xFF4D0D08/} can be obtained from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Crimson Mace Mummies{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Belkan Sanctuary{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. Get 20 for Hime.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tell Hime in Moonlight Shore Village the required ingredients

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Grave Keeper Larell has been trying to find out how to create sleeping pills since Hime was asking him about it a few days ago. Larell found how he made them before in an old medical book and he would like you to deliver the ingredient list to {C=0xFF00863C/}Hime{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Moonlight Shore Village{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain 15 Poisonous Pumpkins from Pumpkin Heads in Dangerous Caverns

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tool Merchant Hime is creating a sleeping pill so he can capture an eagle as a pet. According to Larell's recipe 15 Poisonous Pumpkins are required. You can obtain {C=0xFFFF5917/}Poisonous Pumpkins{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Pumpkin Heads{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Dangerous Caverns{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Obtain Skull Blood from Barrel Bones in Dangerous Caverns

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Hime

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Tool Merchant Hime is creating a sleeping pill to capture a pet bird. Hime needs to include 5 Skull Blood in the pill to attract an eagle to it.
You can obtain 5 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Skull Bloods{C=0xFF4D0D08/} from {C=0xFFFF5917/}Barrel Bones{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Dangerous Caverns{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Retrieve the Mercenaries Note from Shroom Soldiers in Dangerous Caverns

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - Thomas

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Mercenary Leader Thomas says he lost a contract for his mercenary clan while he was in Dangerous Caverns. Help Thomas out, go to {C=0xFF016295/}Dangerous Caverns{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and find the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mercenary Note{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, one of the {C=0xFFFF5917/}Shroom Soldiers{C=0xFF4D0D08/} is the most likely culprit.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
 Speak with Leo in Port of the Winds

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Banker Sofia heard a bad story about {C=0xFF00863C/}Leo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Port of the Winds{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
Deliver a message to Leo from Sofia to Leo know he is not alone.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
 Speak with Jeremy in Port of the Winds

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of Winds - Jeremy

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Leo would like to express his appreciation and love to his Grandpa Jeremy who has been taking care of him. Leo is too shy to tell him by himself however, so he's asked you to let {C=0xFF00863C/}Jeremy{C=0xFF4D0D08/} know how he feels.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Speak with Leo at Port of the Winds.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Port of the Winds - Leo

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Sage Jeremy was really touched hearing that his grandson, Leo, sent you to say how much he loved him.
Jeremy would also like to tell Leo how much he loves him too. Go to {C=0xFF00863C/}Leo{C=0xFF4D0D08/} and pass on the message.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat Fist Dudu Dangerous Caverns

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - James

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
James, a master of investment is trying to become rich by buying and selling land. This time James has found some good land, but Fist Dudus are living there.
Help James out by defeating 20 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Fist Dudus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} at {C=0xFF016295/}Dangerous Caverns{C=0xFF4D0D08/}. He can't do anything with the land until they are gone.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest Requirements]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 50 Dudu in Dangerous Caverns

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - James

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
James went to show the land to his investors. While they were taking a look around they were all attacked by Dudus! During the attack one of the investors, William, was injured.
Help James calm down, and show the Dudus a lesson by defeating 50 {C=0xFFFF5917/}Dudus{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, {C=0xFFFF5917/}Fist Dudus{C=0xFF4D0D08/}, and {C=0xFFFF5917/}Mage Dudus{C=0xFF4D0D08/} in {C=0xFF016295/}Dangerous Caverns{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Requirement]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Defeat 100 monsters in Dangerous Caverns

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Quest NPC]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
Moonlight Shore Village - James

{T=FTcts_13/C=0xFFA62700/}[Detail]{T=QTtext/C=0xFF4D0D08/}
James took revenge on the Dudus for injuring his investor William. William was impressed with the way his injuries were avenged and is willing to invest in the area if the monsters are removed.
Defeat 100 of any monster in {C=0xFF016295/}Dangerous Caverns{C=0xFF4D0D08/}.
